title: leftover vegetable soup
directions: Don't
throw away those leftovers.
Put them all into a freezer-safe
container and freeze them!
When you have sufficient vegetables, meats and/or gravies, place in a large pot. Add cooked,
whole tomatoes with juice, tomato sauce and soup stock. Add
seasoning, onion, potatoes, carrots and any other vegetables desired.
Bring to a boil;	reduce heat and simmer until fresh vegetables are done.

title: easy meat marinade(for steaks or chicken)
directions: Coat steak or chicken with TexJoy steak seasoning. Cover meat with Italian dressing. Place meat in a plastic bag and seal. Store in refrigerator overnight or longer.

title: fuzzy navel punch
directions: Mix and serve in punch bowl.
Add crushed ice or float an ice ring.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Peel and mash.
Then beat with electric hand mixer until smooth and fluffy.

Add beaten eggs, sugar, milk, melted butter and spices. Mix well. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, checking for doneness or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pick-a-part cake
directions: Quarter biscuits.
Shake in 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Put in ungreased tube pan.
Melt margarine and 1 cup of sugar, bring to a boil until thick.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Turn out of pan immediately (be careful).

title: quick and easy lemonade pie
directions: Thaw lemonade mix, add directly to condensed milk.
Using mixer, beat until smooth.
Add lemon juice and rind, if desired. Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine mushroom soup, onion soup, rice and water in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Put chicken breasts on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: yummy brownies
directions: Cut 1-inch (not to be used) of a stick of butter and melt the larger portion. Add brown sugar, flour, soda, egg and vanilla. Mix together and add pecans and chocolate chips. Bake at 350°.

title: my mother's fried chicken
directions: Soak chicken pieces in cold water for several hours to remove blood.
Drain.
Place flour in plastic bag for coating chicken. Heat vegetable shortening in an iron skillet, hot enough so chicken will start frying the minute you add it to the fat.
Fry until brown on both sides.
When brown, season with salt and pepper. Cover and cook slowly until tender.
Remove lid and fry until crisp on both sides.
Remove chicken to heated serving platter.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and serve.

title: apple crunch
directions: Put apples in a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup of sugar mixture over apples. Remove crust from bread and cut into cubes.

title: home made croutons
directions: In a bowl:
Toss cubes with olive oil, parmesan cheese, garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.

title: spinach things
directions: Mix, spread, roll and cut.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend in buttermilk.
Pour into pastry shells.
Bake in a 350° oven.
Pie should brown.

title: fried tuna patties
directions: Add all ingredients and pat into patties.
Fry in vegetable oil or olive oil.
Fill pan with oil just enough to cover the bottom.
Fry until golden brown on both sides (about 10 minutes cooking time).

title: blueberry strata pie
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve the syrup.
Blend cream cheese and the next 3 ingredients.
Set aside 2 Tbsp. pineapple.
Stir in remaining pineapple into cream cheese mixture.
Spread over the graham cracker crust and chill.
Blend sugar, cornstarch, salt and 1/3 c. pineapple syrup.
Cook until thickened over low heat.
Add the blueberries and cook a little longer.
Cool.
Pour over the chilled pie crust.
Top with cool whip and reserved pineapple.

title: mom's poor man cake
directions: Mix sugar, raisins and water in saucepan and boil for 5 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pink velvet salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: spicy oatmeal cake
directions: In mixing bowl gradually add sugar to butter, creaming well. Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Add oats mixture.
Mix well.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Add and stir until well blended. Pour batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Frost in pan with Lazy Daisy Frosting.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Slice ends from bread.
Slice remaining loaf into 8 slices and arrange in bottom of two greased (8-inch) square pans.
In large bowl, beat eggs, egg yolks, light cream, brown sugar, pie spice and flavorings.
Gradually add milk, beating until well blended; pour over bread.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: christmas bonbons
directions: Melt last three ingredients in a double boiler and keep hot. Using a toothpick, dip each ball into the chocolate mixture. Place on waxed paper until chocolate has cooled.
Refrigerate.

title: tom's chili
directions: Brown meat and
pour
off liquid.
Bring to a boil with all other ingredients added and then turn heat down and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: cornbread dressing casserole
directions: Add onion, jalapeno and dressing mix to browned meat.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Grease a 10 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add onion, eggs and oil.
Mix well together, then add zucchini.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until lightly browned on top.

title: thin layer chocolate cake
directions: Add together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix dry ingredients into margarine, sugar and eggs alternately with milk.
Put 1 cup of mixture in 10-inch griddle.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: italian fondue
directions: Brown ground turkey in saucepan; drain off fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Add cheeses gradually. Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Blend together wine and cornstarch.
Add to cheese mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Transfer to fondue pot and place over fondue burner.
Spear bread cubes with fondue fork. Dip into fondue mixture, swirling to coat.

title: old-fashioned donuts
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating well. Blend in shortening.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to sugar and eggs.
Chill dough (2 to 3 hours) until it can be rolled and cut.
Roll 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut with donut cutter and fry in hot oil, a few at a time, turning once until light brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix and make into small balls or medium.
Roll in shredded coconut.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Very rich.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Cut the cake into slices and place in oblong dish.
Mix the vanilla pudding with the milk until it is thick.
Pour over cake and spread.
Chill.
Put the blueberry pie filling over the pudding.
Chill again, then spread the Cool Whip over the berries and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar. Add the molasses and egg; beat well. Sift together and add the flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and ginger. Beat until smooth. Use ice tea spoon to scoop up dough, then roll into small balls and dip in granulated sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° about 15 minutes.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut each squash in half.
Remove seeds and fibers.
Pare squash; cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Stir together sugar, margarine, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Arrange squash in baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches).
Top with apples. Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: chocolate sack
directions: Thaw pastry 20 minutes.
Preheat oven to 425°.
On a lightly floured board, roll pastry to a 14-inch square.
In the center of the square, place chocolate, walnuts and butter; sprinkle with Grand Marnier.
Pull pastry edges together, twist and turn.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake for 20 minutes.
Let stand at least 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and serve. Serves 6.

title: lindsey's sweet potato pies
directions: Boil the potatoes with skins on until tender with cover on. Drain and peel the potatoes. Thoroughly mash the sweet potatoes with electric mixer.
Mix in butter until melted.
Add sugar, evaporated milk, nutmeg, vanilla and eggs.
Mix with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour sweet potato mixture into the pie crusts.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until knife inserted off center comes out clean.

title: fruit salad
directions: Place all fruit with its own juice into bowl.
Other fresh fruit can be added.
Sprinkle pudding over top and stir to dissolve.
Place in fridge.
I like to serve this with angel food cake.
Also good with pound cake or eat as is.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12-inch Bundt pan.
Blend cake mix, pudding mix, club soda, oil and eggs in a large bowl of electric mixer.
Beat until well blended.
Pour batter in prepared pan. Bake for 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Invert on wire rack and cool completely. Sprinkle confectioners sugar over the top of cake.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Cook ground beef until it crumbles.
Drain fat, then put meat in a colander.
Rinse with hot water to remove any extra fat. Place all ingredients in a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Simmer until barley is done.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl combine shortening, sugars and vanilla; beat creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in M&M's.
Roll into small balls and lay on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Mix margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk as needed.
Add vanilla and lemon.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In baking pan (9 x 13-inch), mix celery soup with water and rice.
Lay chicken pieces on top of mixture.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Pour over top the mushroom soup mixed with water.
Bake uncovered for 2 hours at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: as simple as can be cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; peel and dice.
Fry diced bacon until almost done; drain.
Combine ingredients except for olives and bacon and place in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top with olives and bacon and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Do not cover.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and salt until fluffy; gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then confectioners sugar until smooth.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on baking sheets.
Chill until firm.
With fork or wooden pick, dip each into melted candy coating, not coating completely; let excess candy coating drip off.
Place on wax paper-lined baking sheets; let stand or chill until firm.
Store covered at room temperature or in refrigerator.
These candies freeze well.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Place broken pretzels in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over pretzels.
Stir to coat the pretzels evenly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes while baking.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt chips and condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat. Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread into square pan.
Chill for 2 hours, until firm.

title: best bran muffins
directions: Mix wet ingredients and sugar.
Mix dry ingredients and then mix with wet ingredients. Do not overmix.
Pour into muffin tins sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Batter will be thin and should be stored in refrigerator if not baked immediately.
Keeps 1 week or more and can be baked as needed.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and whipping cream until soft peaks form. Stir in other ingredients, except peaches.
Refrigerate several hours until salad sets.

title: nuts and bolts chex mix
directions: In a large baking pan or roaster, carefully mix cereals, pretzels and nuts.
Hard pulverize marjoram and savory and blend with other seasonings.
Blend with cereals.
Cut butter in small chunks over entire surface.
Place in 250° oven for 45 minutes. Stir during toasting.
Store in airtight container.

title: old fashioned sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream
sugar and butter.
Add sour cream and eggs.
Add flavorings.
Sift
dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Dough
will be soft.
Chill several hours.
Roll out small amounts
at
a
time	on
a
well floured surface.
Keep remaining
dough chilled.
Use desired cookie cutters.
Bake 8 to 10	minutes
in 350° oven.	Do not brown the cookies.
This is a very tender soft cookie.
Frost and decorate as desired.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add soup and other ingredients. Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: amish fried potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Cool thoroughly.
Peel and grate with a large carrot grater.
Fry in hot Wesson oil until brown on both sides.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Cover for a few minutes, then serve.

title: louise's corn casserole
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put applesauce into large pie plate.
Mix next 3 ingredients. Sprinkle over applesauce.
Bake in oven or microwave until applesauce bubbles through.

title: easy english trifle
directions: Soak banana slices in pineapple juice. Mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add pudding mix and remaining 1 1/2 cups milk. Beat on low speed 1 minute. Layer 1/2 of cake, fruit and pudding mixture, then layer of Cool Whip; repeat layers. Cover and refrigerate.

title: black forest pudding
directions: In small mixing bowl combine the fresh or frozen cherries and 1/2 cup whipped topping; set aside.
Using 2 cups milk, prepare pudding according to package directions but do not chill.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine thawed potatoes, butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese. Stir well. Spoon into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add flour to make a thick batter. Mix well.
Add softened yeast and eggs.
Beat well.
Add enough more flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured board or pastry cloth and knead until smooth and satiny.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled (about 1 1/2 hours).
When light, punch down.
Cover and let rise 10 minutes.
Roll dough out on board and cut with round cutters. Place each roll in buttered pan, just barely touching each other. Brush with butter.
Let rise until doubled (45 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Warm soup.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Mix gelatin/water into soup; cool.
With hand mixer, mix cooled soup/gelatin and all remaining ingredients, except shrimp.
Chop shrimp very fine in food processor and fold into mixture.
Pour into 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Serve with Ritz or favorite crackers.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix pecans, flour and butter together.
Press into oblong baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: economy sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender. Blend well. Store in refrigerator until used. May be used in any recipe calling for sweetened condensed milk.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll in balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 310° and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: rice chantilly
directions: Combine rice, sour cream, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup of cheese. Spoon into buttered dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in a frypan in the oil. Dissolve chicken cubes in the 1 1/2 cups of boiling water and then add the other ingredients. Pour over pork chops in electric frying pan. Bring to a boil then simmer (with the lid on) for 1 hour or until done.

title: garden vegetable soup
directions: Heat butter and oil in a large kettle.
Add carrots, celery, onion and garlic; saute until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes, oregano, basil, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer vegetable mixture 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add broth, green beans and zucchini; simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon into soup bowls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Combine mustard and honey in a small bowl.
Stir in dill and orange peel.
Line a baking sheet with foil.
Place chicken, skin-side down; brush sauce on top of chicken, coating well.
Turn chicken over; gently pull back skin and brush meat with sauce; replace skin over sauce.
Brush skin with remaining sauce.
Bake at 400 degrees until juices run clear when thickest portion of meat is pierced with a knife, about 30 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Chop all ingredients in blender.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef in oil with onion and garlic.
Add tomato paste, 2 cups water, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: instant pumpkin pie
directions: Combine milk and pudding mix. Beat 1 minute. Will be thick. Add pumpkin and spices. Beat 1 minute longer. Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate 2 hours. Garnish and serve with whipped cream. Yields 8 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in pot.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Cook chicken on grill.
After chicken is about one-half done, dip in sauce and return to grill.
Repeat a couple of times.

title: lo-cal chicken stir-fry
directions: Saute chicken in oil.
Season with garlic salt.
Add vegetables.
Mix broth, cornstarch and ginger.
Pour into stir-fry until thickened.
Serves 3 (282 calories per serving).
Serve over white rice.

title: currey's casserole
directions: Place spinach in strainer, rinse with hot water.
Press out water.
Saute beef, add salt, mushrooms and onion.
Remove from heat.
Add spinach, sour cream and seasonings.
Add 1/2 cup of each cheese.
Put in 2 quart casserole and add cheese on top. Bake at 350 degrees at 20-25 minutes.
Serves 6-8.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Saute seafood in olive oil, garlic and parsley over medium heat for about 3 minutes.
When cool, chop into small pieces.
In a large bowl, add seafood mix, garlic from pan, Ricotta, Romano, salt, pepper, fresh lemon juice and egg; mix well.
Cook shells according to directions, then put in lukewarm water for 10 minutes.
In same saute pan, add butter, heavy cream and 1/2 cup Romano cheese over medium heat and whisk.
Cook until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Put 1/2 white sauce on bottom of pan.
Fill shells with seafood mixture.
Pour rest of sauce over top.
Top with a little Romano.
Bake, covered, until heated, about 25 minutes at 350°.
You may vary seafood for your likes and dislikes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Serve.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix water, sugar and Kool-Aid well.
Mix frozen juices with 3 cans water.
Mix all and freeze.
Take out of freezer in morning to use that night (12 hours).

title: fresh collard or turnip greens
directions: When selecting turnip greens, salad turnips are best.
If you prefer turnips with roots, however choose those with purple topped roots.
Turnips and Collards must be carefully washed.
Fresh greens are best when cooked with fresh pork, backbone, ham hocks, chops or turkey.
Meat gives the greens a down home flavor.
Bring the meat to a boil in 2 to 3 cups of water.
Add tsp. of salt, lemon pepper, dash wine vinegar and red pepper.
Let meat simmer for 30 minutes.
Add vegetable to meat and broth and bring to a broil.
Add another tsp. lemon pepper and salt and 1/2 cup onion (green onion chopped is best or Vidalia onion), and a pinch of sugar.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to an hour.
Serve over rice.

title: banana cookies
directions: On wax paper or in a bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder and baking soda.
In a medium bowl with an electric beater, beat the banana until pureed, there will be 1/2 cup.
Add the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla; at medium or high speed, beat until blended.
Add flour mixture; at low speed, beat until blended.
Add flour mixture; at low speed beat until blended. Drop by level tablespoonfuls a few inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with sugar-cinnamon mixture.

title: walnut glory cake
directions: Sift flour with cinnamon and salt in bowl.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites with an electric mixer until soft mounds form. Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar.
Continue beating until very stiff, straight peaks form.
Do not underbeat.

title: easy prize winning pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Stir in flavoring.
Bake in well-greased, floured 10-inch tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Yields 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: chicken file gumbo
directions: Cut chicken in pieces; wash and wipe dry. Season well with salt and pepper; brown in hot cooking oil. Remove chicken; sift flour into hot oil and brown. Add onion and cook for 2 minutes. Add chicken, hot water, and a few grains of cayenne pepper; simmer until chicken is tender. Add oyster or shrimp and parsley; simmer 20 minutes. Remove from heat and serve with steamed rice.

title: pecan butter balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Gradually add flour, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Cover and chill until firm.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes or until lightly brown. Remove from sheet and cool.
Yield:
3 dozen cookies.

title: flounder
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Cut flounder in serving size pieces.
Melt margarine and saute onion. Stir in flour and cook until bubbly.
Add milk; cook until thick. Stir in salt, pepper and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour over fish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: cherry malts
directions: Soften ice cream.
Add milk and juice from cherries.
Chop up all the cherries, except 12 to 15.
Add to ice cream.
Mix with a mixer.
Pour into glasses.
Top with whipped cream and cherry. Makes about 12 to 15 servings.

title: georgia cornbread
directions: Option:
Can use 1 egg plus more water.

title: yabba dabba doo squares
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal and toss to coat well.
Press firmly into greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Store in cool place.
Makes 24 squares.

title: chocolate toffee crescent bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent dough into 2 large rectangles.
Place in ungreased cookie sheet.
Gently press dough to cover bottom of pan.
Seal perforations.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer 1/2 cake, pineapple, pudding, Strawberry Glaze, Cool Whip, coconut and pecans, then the other half of ingredients in the same order.
Garnish top with Cool Whip and large strawberries.

title: chocolate delite pudding
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with flour and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13 inch oven-proof dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool completely.
Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and 1 c. Cool Whip; spread on cooled crust.
Mix milk, pudding and vanilla; spread on cream cheese mixture.
Place remaining Cool Whip on top. Garnish with pecan halves or shaved curls of chocolate.

title: vegetable stir-fry(microwave)
directions: Combine oil, garlic, onion and mushrooms in microwave dish. Microwave on High uncovered for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in vegetables. Cover with lid.
Microwave for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes. Stir once.

title: ice cream sandwich
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg, shortening, margarine, vanilla and 1/2 cake mix until smooth.
Stir in remaining mix.
Divide dough in 4 parts.
Roll each into rectangle (10 x 6-inch) on lightly floured cloth covered board.
Cut into 3 x 3 1/2-inch pieces each.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until edges look set, centers will be slightly puffed.
Prick surfaces with fork.
Cool and remove from sheet.
Cut ice cream into rectangles about 3/4 inch thick.
Place between 2 cookies and press together.
Wrap in foil at least 24 hours.

title: dutch cheese wafers
directions: Cream the butter and cream cheese in medium mixing bowl. Gradually add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour and apricots; mix well.
Shape dough into a roll 1 inch in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper; chill at least 3 hours, or until firm.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices; place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yields 6 to 7 dozen.

title: celeste's chicken chow mein
directions: Cook onions and celery until tender.
Stir in soup and chicken stock; heat to boiling.
Combine cornstarch, lemon juice and soy sauce.
Mix until smooth.
Add to soup mixture.
Cook until thick; add chicken and toasted almonds.
Salt and pepper.
Pour chicken chow mein over chow mein noodles.

title: garlic grits
directions: Slowly stir grits and salt into boiling water.
Reduce heat to low and cook until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Add stick of oleo, garlic cheese, sweet milk and eggs.
Place in long baking dish.
Cook about 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with grated cheese and put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut meat diagonally against grain in thin slivers or strips. Cut green peppers into thin strips.
Sear meat over high heat in hot salad oil, stirring quickly.
Add onion, garlic, green peppers and celery.
Add consomme.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Cover and turn heat to moderate and cook 5 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch blended with water and soy sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Serve immediately with freshly boiled rice or brown rice.

title: sage cornmeal bread
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal and baking powder.
In another bowl, mix butter, egg and milk.
Add liquid mix to dry mix and stir until blended.
Stir in corn and sage.
Place in 8 or 9-inch square pan and bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
The top should be golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: hamburger-bean casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together, then put in casserole.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or may be cooked on top of stove for 30 minutes on medium-low heat.

title: fast and easy stuffing
directions: Poultry seasoning may be substituted for parsley and pepper. Saute onion and celery in butter till soft.
Add bread cubes and seasonings.
Add chicken broth to moisten.
Bake if desired.

title: baked chicken
directions: Soak chicken in lemon juice.
Place chicken in shallow glass pan.
Combine salt, pepper and paprika.
Sprinkle over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Cover and bake another 35 minutes, until tender.

title: lemon pie bars
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: gloria's cheese roll(an oriental recipe)
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients. Mix well; cover and chill 1 hour. Finely chop the pecans or peanuts. Combine with chili powder. Pour nuts on wax paper (12 x 12-inch). Form into 3 rolls (or 1 to 3 balls). Roll in nuts. Wrap in waxed paper or plastic and chill. Makes nice holiday gift or treat served with crackers.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Rub spices heavily all over meat, then put on grill.
Cook slowly for 6 to 8 hours.
If wanted, put sauce on when almost done.

title: old settlers' beans
directions: Cook over low heat for about 3 hours in a crock-pot.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Peel and grate cucumber.
Blend with cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise.
Thin with milk.
Season with few drops of lemon juice, garlic salt and white pepper.
Chill and serve with crackers or chips.

title: luscious lemon squares
directions: Stir together 2 cups flour and 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar.
Cut butter into this mixture until crumbly. Pat into 15 x 10-inch nonstick pan.
Bake until set, 10 to 15 minutes.
In medium bowl, beat eggs with remaining flour, baking powder, sugar, orange juice, lemon juice, lemon peel and vanilla. Pour egg mixture over hot crust and bake until top is set, 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar.
Cut into 48 squares.

title: pizza sandwich
directions: Spread 2 tablespoons pizza sauce on each piece of bread; cover with cheese.
Arrange several slices of pepperoni on cheese.
Heat 7 minutes in a 450° oven or just until the cheese begins to melt. Serve with Italian olives and cherry tomatoes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: super deer patties
directions: Mix all
together good.
Make into 8 or 9 patties.
Roll in flour.
Brown in small amount of corn oil in electric skillet, medium hot.
Drain off oil.
Cover each pattie with cream of mushroom soup (special request).
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
This can be simmered in brown gravy or tomato sauce.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: In large pot, saute onion, celery and garlic in butter until just soft.
Add clam broth, water, wine, herbs and fish.
Bring to boil; simmer 10 minutes.
Add scallops; simmer 10 minutes more. Season to taste.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Mix together and spread in jelly roll pan.
Make 20 holes in cake.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix all fruits together.
Add orange juice and stir.
Top with small amount of flaked coconut.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower according to package directions; drain well. Halve any large pieces.
In 2-quart casserole, combine soup, water, mushrooms, onion, basil and salt and pepper.
Carefully stir in cauliflower.
Sprinkle cheese and paprika on top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: three fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, blend cream cheese, salad dressing, lemon juice and sugar. Lightly mix in pineapple, orange sections, cherries, nuts and whipped topping. Pour into a 10 or 12-cup Bundt pan. Cover top tightly with wrap; freeze.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix with 1 egg and butter.
Pat into bottom of greased pan (11 x 13-inch).
Beat 3 eggs well.
Add 1 box powdered sugar and 8 ounces cream cheese.
Mix well.
Pour over top of cake mixture.
May sprinkle with nuts.
Cook slowly at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In buttered 9 x 12-inch dish, place frozen broccoli.
Boil chicken (45 minutes or until done).
Cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Combine soups and sour cream.
Mix in chicken.
Put Cheddar cheese on top of broccoli.
Spread chicken mixture on top of cheese and broccoli.
Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Place on top of meat mixture.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: snack oyster surprise
directions: Combine and continue to stir until oil disappears.
Can put oil on crackers.
Put in oven 5 to 10 minutes.

title: peach pops
directions: In blender or food processor, blend or process the peaches, milk, pineapple juice, lemon peel, lemon juice and vanilla until smooth.
Pour mixture into 4 (6 to 8 ounce) paper cups.
Cover with foil and freeze until partially frozen.
Insert a wooden ice pop stick in the center of each and freeze at least 8 hours or until completely frozen.

title: jalapeno salsa
directions: Combine chopped ingredients in a bowl.
Add the lemon juice and pulp and mix thoroughly.
Refridgerate before serving.
Serve with crisp tortilla chips, on celery stalks or other raw veggies, as a sauce on Tacos or whenever a spicy salsa is desired.

title: cranberry apple cobbler
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Mix all ingredients and spray pan with Pam.
Add ingredients to pan and cover with pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and mashed bananas; beat well.
Add flour, milk and vanilla.
Mix well and stir in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake loaf at 350° for 1 hour or 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water in a pan until it forms a brittle ball when tested in cold water.
Add butter and peanuts.
Cook until mixture is nicely brown.
Before removing from heat, add coconut and soda; stir thoroughly.
When bubbles nearly disappear, pour into buttered shallow pan and cool, then turn up and take back of a tablespoon and break into serving pieces.

title: smoked brisket
directions: Season beef with salt and pepper.
Place in center of large sheet of heavy aluminum foil.
Pour bottle of liquid smoke over meat.
Seal foil tightly and bake at 350° for 4 hours.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix beef, egg, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, salt, pepper and onion.
Form into balls and brown.
Remove from skillet.
Combine oil and juice in skillet until mixed.
Add 3 tablespoons cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar and white sugar, cooking over low heat until mixture thickens.
Add pineapple and green peppers (cut in long strips).
Return meatballs to skillet and warm.
Serve over rice.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Crush potato chips.
Roll chicken in butter and then in crushed chips.
Line pan with foil and lay chicken in pan.
Do not stack and do not cover.
Cook for 1 hour at 325°.
Do not turn.

title: six cup salad
directions: Mix all together and chill several hours or overnight. Garnish with maraschino cherries, if desired.
Pineapple tidbits can be used instead of seedless grapes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Grease pan.
Mix on stove over low heat the soup, sour cream, onion, chili powder, garlic powder, green chilies and 1/2 cup of the Cheddar cheese.
Grease baking dish.
Place
chicken inside tortillas and roll up.
Place half of the mixture in baking dish. Add rolled tortillas across pan.
Add the remaining mixture over the tortillas and top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish. Cover with topping.

title: fruit squares
directions: Cream margarine with sugar and vanilla. Add 1 egg at a time and beat well. Add flour. Put 3/4 of batter on bottom of greased cookie sheet. Add can of pie filling (fruit). Dot rest of batter on top and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet and drain; add salt, pepper and ketchup. heat thoroughly. Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top! Place biscuits on top of the cheese. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Make Rice-A-Roni according to directions on box.
Drain artichokes and save the liquid.
Chop artichokes, onions, olives and green pepper.
Cool the rice.
Mix the mayonnaise with artichoke liquid.
Combine all ingredients and mix.
Add the curry. (You can add curry to mayonnaise and artichoke juice, then mix.)

title: brunch casserole
directions: Trim crusts and cube the bread.
Place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Layer cooked sausage and grated Cheddar on top.
Pour beaten eggs, mixed with milk, over all.
Top with undiluted soup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Should be made night before and refrigerated before baking.

title: green noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Combine with remaining ingredients and bake in well-buttered casserole dish in a moderate oven for one hour. Serves 12.

title: portuguese beans
directions: Cook the beans in large pot.
Add all of ingredients to pot except for wine and tomato paste.
Dilute tomato paste with wine and then pour into pot and salt to taste.
Cook beans an additional 1/2 hour.

title: fruity coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, pineapple, celery, raisins and yogurt in a large bowl.
Toss well; add mandarin oranges, toss again.
Chill for 4 to 6 hours.
Add bananas when ready to serve.
Toss again. Serves 8.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter in heavy 3-quart pan.
Add sugar and salt and stir.
Stir in Karo and mix well.
Gradually add Eagle Brand milk; stir constantly.
Cook to 245°.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan; cool and cut.

title: onion-cheese spread
directions: Cream to soften and blend cheeses.
Add onion juice to taste.

title: fluffy pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine eggs, milk and sour cream; slowly pour into dry ingredients, beating with a whisk to prevent lumping.
Add butter and beat smooth.

title: "jimmy's" rice
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Stir in rice and spinach.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Rinse and scrub potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Use spoon handle under knife so as not to go all the way through.
Put in baking dish.
Slightly spread apart.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 425° or microwave on High 14 minutes.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Brown short ribs in small amount of oil or margarine on all sides; cover with water.
Add salt and pepper and cook until ribs are done.
Add about 3 beef cubes and fresh small cut up vegetables (meat is taken out of pot and cut into small pieces and then put back in pot).
Add frozen vegetables.
Check cooking time for tenderness.
Add tomatoes and rest of seasoning.
Cook until all is tender.
Add seasonings and water as needed or desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion until just tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add sour cream and soup; mix together.
Combine margarine with stuffing mix, stirring until well blended.
Combine half stuffing with squash mixture. Spoon into 2-quart buttered casserole.
Top with remainder of stuffing.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 375° or until bubbly.

title: cannon balls(popcorn)
directions: Pop corn in Crisco, about a dishpan full.
Boil the sugar, molasses and water until reaches hard crack stage (when dropped into ice water).
Takes about 20 minutes stove time and about 12 minutes hard boiling time.
Pour over popped corn, and with greased hands form into balls.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Makes about 16 medium-size balls.

title: sassy cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into small balls.
Fry or broil until brown, turning once.
Drain well. In saucepan saute onions and green peppers until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until sugar is dissolved, then pour over meatballs and simmer slowly, covered, for 15 to 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: ham strata
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with bread slices.
Layer with ham and cheese.
Top with more bread.
Mix in bowl, eggs, evaporated milk, milk and mustard.
Pour over bread and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Last 10 minutes, mix remaining ingredients and spread.
Finish baking.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour on

title: pickled eggs
directions: Peel eggs and put in large mouth jar.
Tie cloves, ginger root and peppercorns in cheesecloth.
Combine vinegar, water and salt in saucepan.
Add spices.
Bring to a boil; cook for 10 minutes. Remove spice bag.
Chill mixture.
Pour over eggs.
Seal jars; let stand for 2 days before serving.

title: chocolate peanut butter candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted chocolate chips over top.
Cool slightly. Cut into squares and serve.

title: biloxi biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll out and cut with a glass top. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a cookie sheet. Using a towel dipped in water and the 1 tablespoon lemon juice, wipe mushrooms clean.
Remove stems; chop them and set mushrooms aside.
To stems, add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pack cavity of mushrooms and place on cookie sheet.
Add a few drops of oil to each mushroom.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F (165°C). Grease and flour two 8-inch round cake pans. In a medium bowl, cream together the butter, white sugar and brown sugar. Stir in the eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder; stir into the creamed mixture. Finally, stir in the vanilla, carrots, pineapple and walnuts. Divide batter evenly between the two pans. Don't worry about filling them too full, as this cake does not rise very much. Bake for 60 to 75 minutes in the preheated oven. Test for doneness with a toothpick or knife.

title: mango sorbet
directions: Place sugar and water in medium saucepan over medium heat. Stir to dissolve sugar.
Pour into bowl; cool.
Add mango puree and lime juice.
Mix.
Chill until very cold.
Freeze in ice cream freezer as manufacturer directs.

title: basic barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add brown sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and water.
Simmer for a few minutes.
If sauce is too dry, after your meat is added, add additional 1/3 cup ketchup and 1/3 cup water.
Serves 2 (but can be doubled).

title: texas baked beans
directions: Cook bacon.
Saute onion in margarine.
Combine with brown sugar and catsup.
Add beans.
Mix all together and bake in 2 1/2-quart baking dish at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: trade winds salad(serving size: 6 to 8)
directions: Prepare macaroni.
Drain pineapple chunks.
Reserve 2 tablespoons.
In medium skillet, melt margarine and 2 teaspoons brown sugar.
Add luncheon meat and cook until browned, and coated with sugar mixture.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
In medium bowl, combine macaroni, luncheon meat mixture, pineapple chunks, cheese and green pepper.

title: dinner loaf *
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; saute onion and Kasha until onion is transparent.
Add water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat.
Cook about 15 minutes, until water is absorbed.

Cook spinach and put spinach, peanuts and one egg in blender and process on high until creamed (nuts should be coarse). Lightly beat one egg; add spinach mixture, Kasha, salt and pepper. Put into well oiled 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°. Cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: homemade cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease large baking sheet and set aside.
Use a pastry blender to cut butter into flour until it resembles corn meal; add remaining ingredients and stir to mix well.
Do not overmix.
Drop by rounded tablespoons, 2-inches apart on baking sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 18 biscuits.

title: wild bill's pinto bean chili
directions: Place beans in a large heavy saucepan or Dutch oven and cover with water and bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Return beans to the pan and cover with water by 2 inches.
Add all the remaining ingredients except the meat and salt.
Bring mixture back to a boil.
After the beans have reached boiling, turn the heat down to simmer.
Saute meat until browned. Add to the bean mixture.
Cook until the beans are soft, stirring occasionally and making sure that the beans have enough water and do not dry out.
Cook about 3 to 4 hours.
Uncover if the beans get too soupy.
Add salt to taste.
Garnish with shredded Jack or Cheddar cheese and cilantro.
Serve with fresh flour tortillas and your favorite salsa.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters.
Combine cracker crumbs, pepper and butter. Sprinkle 1/3 of mixture in a buttered baking dish.
Cover with half of oysters.
Repeat layers.
Pour mushroom soup over oyster mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over the top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in 3 layers (8-inch pans) or 2 layers (9-inch pans) at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
If Bundt pan is used, bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and peanut butter in mixer until smooth.
Add 12 ounces Cool Whip, mixing until fluffy. Pour into pie shells and top with more topping.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: granny's sour cream pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook the mixture on stove top until thickened.
Cool a little, then put into cooked pie shell.
Use egg whites to make meringue topping.

title: chewy charlies
directions: Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add 1/4 teaspoon vanilla, 3/4 cup peanut butter and stir until dissolved.
Add 3 cups oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: mother-in-law salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, 7-Up, marshmallows, water, bananas and pineapple; let congeal.

title: spunky spareribs
directions: Place ribs meaty sides down in shallow pan.
Roast in 450° oven for 30 minutes; drain off fat.
Turn ribs and roast 30 minutes more.
Drain off fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; brush on ribs.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Roast ribs covered for 1 hour or until tender; brush with sauce occasionally.

title: mulled cider
directions: In 2-quart measure, combine all ingredients.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 1/2 minutes.
Strain and pour into serving cups.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Make sugar cookies except before baking, paint designs on the cookies with "Egg Yolk Paint."

title: lynne's great cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese.
Cook ground beef and sausage.
Mix altogether slowly.
Cook for about 15 minutes.

title: magic caramel icing
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil. Stir constantly until forms a soft ball. Remove form heat and beat with mixer until creamy. Add to top of cake.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil sweet potatoes; mash.
Mix the next 7 ingredients with potatoes.
Put into a 9-inch square (or equivalent) casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour, butter and pecans and crumble over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Absolutely delicious!
Great with turkey, ham, chicken and pork.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Use 2 or 3 teaspoons "tea" per serving.

title: bacon and egg spaghetti
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed.
Drain.
Keep warm.
In a large skillet, cook bacon.
Remove onto paper towels.
In drippings in skillet, cook onions until tender (about 5 minutes).
Add spaghetti and bacon to onions.
Toss until well mixed.
Stir in eggs and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls of mixture to 1 cup boiling water.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Let set for 1 hour.
Use with any crackers.

title: refried bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

This may be cooked in a crock-pot on low for a few hours or may be baked in a 2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes, or until cheese is completely melted. Stir before serving and serve with nacho chips.
May also be cooked in the microwave.

title: aunt della's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If potatoes are too thick add a little milk.
Put in baking dish and cook until bubbly at 400 degrees.
Dot with marshmallows. Continue baking until marshmallows brown.

title: chicken with wine
directions: Dip chicken breasts in milk and flavored bread crumbs.
Fry in oil.
Remove from pan.
Add garlic and onion to pan drippings. Saute until soft.
Add wine and bring to boil.
Blend cornstarch with broth and add to pan.
Bring to boil and add mustard.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Put chicken in baking pan and pour sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: grilled turkey shish kabob
directions: Cut turkey tenderloins into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Mix next 4 ingredients; pour over turkey cubes.
Toss to coat; refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Thread turkey and vegetables alternately on skewers.
Brush lightly with oil. Broil or grill 6-inches from heat or coals for 10 minutes.
Turn and brush occasionally with marinade.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients except rice.
Stir in rice.
Bake in greased casserole, covered at 325° for 1 1/4 hours until set. Uncover last few minutes to brown top.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Thin this mixture with
milk
and
pour
into a 2 quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Cook
bacon.
Brown meat (which has been sprinkled with salt, pepper and flour) in bacon fat.
Add 3 tablespoons flour and juice from tomatoes.
Stir until thickened.
Add tomatoes, other vegetables,
tarragon and basil leaves to taste.
Bake, covered, at 275° to 300° for 4 to 6 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy breakfast strata
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix eggs and milk well.
Place broken bread on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle cooked meat on top of bread and then shredded cheese.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake at 350° until set and brown around edges.

title: pork chops hawaiian
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper. Dust with flour. Heat oil and brown chops.
Place pork chops in an 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Place a slice of pineapple on each pork chop. Arrange carrots around pork chops. Add water and cover. Cook over low heat in oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add more water, if needed.

title: basic barbecue sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients in a saucepan for 1/2 hour.
Add meat and cook until heated through.
(Great for leftover turkey.)

title: instant hot cocoa
directions: Mix well all ingredients; store in a tight container.
To serve, place 1/2 cup of mixture in cup and fill with hot water.

title: chocolate milkshake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend on low until smooth.
Pour into 2 large glasses.
Serve right away.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box. Pour 1/2 in greased and floured pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels and milk over low heat. Pour over baked cake. Sprinkle chips and nuts. Pour remaining batter over top. Bake 17 to 20 additional minutes.

title: fruit pie
directions: Put fruit in baking dish.
Slice butter over fruit.
Mix flour, sugar and cream.
Pour over fruit.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Beat egg yolks, slightly. Stir into mixture.
Stir in milk.
Cook in saucepan on medium heat until thick.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Put meringue on top and brown in oven.

title: swiss cheese bread
directions: Trim top and side crusts from bread, leaving bottom crust intact.
Make diagonal cuts, 1-inch thick, through the bread but not through the bottom.
Combine all remaining ingredients. Spread half the butter mixture between bread slices.
Use remaining mixture to frost top and sides of bread.
Place bread in foil boat; cover loosely with another sheet of foil.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.
For last 5 minutes, remove foil to allow bread to brown.
Yield:
18 to 24 servings.

title: mom's grape-nuts pudding
directions: Heat 1 cup milk and pour over Grape-Nuts.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Add 3 cups milk to mixture and stir.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top once mixture has been poured into casserole dish. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Pudding is done when tested and knife comes out clean.

title: quick and easy quiche
directions: Prick bottom of pie crust and prebake for 5 minutes in 400° oven.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in pan. Sprinkle with seasoning salt and garlic salt.
Then pour soup over pork chops. Add enough water to cover bottom of pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana medley
directions: Mix all ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Pour mixture into 8-cup oiled mold and freeze at least 3 hours or until firm. Unmold; let stand about 20 minutes at room temperature before serving.
Decorate with whipped cream and peach slices.
Serves 12.

title: jalapeno delight
directions: Line bottom of a casserole dish with jalapeno peppers.
Cover with the cheese.
Beat eggs and pour over mixture.
Next, pour whole kernel corn over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: swedish brownies
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar and beat. Melt butter (or margarine) and add to eggs and sugar along with flour, salt, and flavoring. Beat well. Put in an 8 inch squared greased pan and sprinkle top with sliced almonds and granulated sugar. Bake 325 degrees for about 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean. Recipe can be doubled.

title: pickled eggs
directions: When the last pickled beet has been consumed from 2 or 3 jars, keep the pickling liquid.
Hard boil 1/2 dozen eggs.
Peel the eggs and place them in the beet pickle solution.
Close the jars and refrigerate for 48 hours.
The resulting pickled eggs will be a real taste treat.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together sugar, oil, eggs and water.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in pumpkin.
Fold in nuts.
Grease and flour 4 (1-pound) coffee cans.
Fill half full and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: pumpkin-pear soup
directions: Cook pears and onion in butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add pear mixture and pumpkin. Process until smooth.
Transfer pumpkin mixture to a large saucepan; add chicken broth and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes; remove cinnamon stick.
Stir in half and half and heat thoroughly (do not boil).
Garnish, if desired.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: southern fried dill pickles
directions: Combine eggs, 1/4 cup flour, milk, worcestershire sauce, cayenne pepper, and garlic powder in bowl.
Stir well.
In separate bowl combine cornmeal, 2 cups flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Drop pickles into milk mixture and dredge in flour mixture.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: marinated cucumbers and onions
directions: Mix cucumbers and onions with salt and soak for 1 hour.
Drain and set aside.
Mix all remaining ingredients and add to cucumbers and onions.
Keep refrigerated.
Will keep several days.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Toss real good. Serve on lettuce leaf. Refrigerate overnight.

title: claire's chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions, shortening cooking time by 5 minutes.
Saute onion in melted butter.
Combine rice and onion with remaining ingredients.
Pour into a buttered (3-quart) baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: white clam sauce(salsa di vongole)
directions: Drain clams, reserving liquid; set aside.
In skillet, slowly heat oil and butter.
Add garlic and saute until golden.
Remove from heat.
Stir in clam liquid, parsley and salt; bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered 10 minutes.
Add clams; simmer 3 minutes.
Pour over a pound (16 ounces) of spaghetti or linguini.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix pineapple and marshmallows; set aside about 1 hour.
Add pudding and stir until blended.
Add Cool Whip and mix all together.

title: warm german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done but firm.
Cool; remove skins.
Cut bacon into small pieces; fry until crisp, then drain.
Return 1/4 cup bacon fat to pan.
Saute vegetables.
Stir in sugar, flour, salt and pepper.
Add vinegar and water; cook until thick.
Slice skinned potatoes into bowl.
Add bacon.
Pour sauce over potatoes; mix lightly.
Serve warm.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: To layer, line a 2-quart casserole dish with chopped lettuce. Combine onions and celery to form second layer.
Third layer, drained peas.
Spread out Hellmann's mayonnaise to form next layer. Next place sliced eggs and then crumbled bacon.
Final layer, sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving for best flavor.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar. Beat in 2 eggs at a time, then add flour until all is used.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Turn into tube pan, greased with margarine.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Do not open oven during baking time.

title: colleen's earthquake cake
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer the coconut, pecans and cake mix in the order listed.
Mix together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine and spoon on top (stay 1-inch inside of edges). Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: flying saucers
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and kidney beans.
Drop tortillas in hot grease just to soften.
Alternate tortilla, hamburger combo, lettuce, cheese, onion and tomato on plate.
Garnish with sour cream, salsa, hot or mild taco sauce.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and cream cheese.
Add vanilla and eggs; blend with electric beater.
Add flour and baking powder; continue mixing.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken.
When done, pull off bone and place in bottom of baking dish.
Combine cream of chicken soup, sour cream and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken in baking dish. Crush Ritz crackers and spread over top.
Drop spoons of butter on top of crackers.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together and add enough buttermilk to make dough.
Drop hush puppies in grease until browned.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, green pepper, seasonings and butter. Marinate with French dressing.
Blend with half of mayonnaise.

title: mexican nachos
directions: Combine process cheese spread, onion and milk in saucepan; stir over low heat until cheese spread is melted.
Cover serving platter with chips; top with lettuce, tomato, olives and cheese spread mixture.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bobby's possum
directions: First catch possum. Parboil possum whole about 1 hour or until tender.
Rub salt and pepper all over.
Put in large roaster pan. Put potatoes around it and bake at 300° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra tightly in jars.
Add to packed okra garlic button, hot pepper and dill seed.
Heat to boiling the water, vinegar and canning salt.
Pour over okra.
Seal.
Let stand 4 weeks.

title: best ever lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and
cornstarch together in a pan.
Add the 2 cups of	water
and
cook
over	moderate heat, stirring until slightly thickened.	(May be cooked in microwave.) Combine egg yolks with juice
and	beat.
Stir a small amount of hot cornstarch mixture into yolks.
Stir all of yolks into cornstarch mixture.
Cook until
thick,
stirring frequently.
Add lemon extract, butter and
vinegar.
Pour
into
pie
shell and let cool.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: spinach souffle(preparation time: 45 minutes)
directions: Put in saucepan 3 tablespoons butter and 1 teaspoon onion. Cook slowly until yellow. Add 3 tablespoons flour; blend well and add 1 cup milk. Add 1 cup chopped spinach; stir in 3 well beaten egg yolks. Cook slowly for 1 minute.
Season to taste and cool 10 minutes. Beat until stiff 3 egg whites and fold gently into spinach mixture. Bake at 350° until firm (approximately 30 minutes).

title: cheese wafer
directions: Mix altogether, roll in 1-inch ball.
Put on cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 minutes or until bottoms are slightly brown.

title: watergate salad:
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: best banana bread or cake
directions: Mix well and bake in greased and floured large loaf pan or 2 small loaf pans at 350° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and bake for 50 minutes more.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 cup pecans.
Shape into one or two balls and chill well.
When thoroughly chilled, roll in the reserved 1 cup of pecans.
Serve with your favorite chips or crackers.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Put vegetables in greased casserole (9 x 12-inch) dish.
Mix onions, celery, mayonnaise and cheese.
Spread over vegetables. Melt oleo and mix with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hello dollies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Use 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt butter in pan. Stir in cracker crumbs. Pat down crumbs in pan. Layer chocolate chips, coconut and pecans. Add Eagle Brand milk over all of this. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Follow Refrigerator Yeast Rolls recipe, then roll 1/3 of dough into a 14 x 10-inch rectangle.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and ground cinnamon.
Roll up, starting at long end. Cut crosswise into 3/4-inch thick slices.
Place in 2 lightly greased 9-inch round cake pans.
Let rise and bake as directed on Refrigerator Yeast Rolls recipe.

title: mexican soup
directions: Brown meat and onion in a large container.
Add remaining ingredients (undrained).
Mix well.
Simmer until blended to taste.

title: cheese 'n eggplant pie
directions: Broil eggplant slices 3 to 5 minutes on each side.
Remove eggplant.
Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cheeses.
In a 9-inch pie pan, arrange eggplant.
Overlap by pressing edges to form a "pie crust."
Spread vegetables evenly over eggplant; sprinkle with oregano and garlic powder.
Top with combined cheeses, then sprinkle Parmesan.
Bake until cheese is melted; brown 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into 4 equal wedges and serve 2 wedges per portion.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, green pepper and onion in large bowl.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons pickling salt over mixture in bowl and distribute. Set in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Drain well.
Then mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Place cucumbers in freezer containers, tightly packed.
Cover with syrup (just enough to cover).
Leave 1-inch headspace.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix sugar and spices.
Add squash, slightly beaten eggs and milk gradually.
Pour mixture into an unbaked 9-inch pie crust and bake at 450° for 10 minutes to set the rim.
Turn oven down to 350° and finish baking for about 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat the cheese until soft.
Gradually add sugar until mixture is smooth.
Stir in vanilla and liquid.
Frosts a 10-inch Bundt cake.

title: chocolate pizza(kids of all ages love this!)
directions: Melt chocolate chips with 14 ounces white chocolate in large saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Heat slowly until all is mixed.
Pour in large baking dish. Place cut-up chicken on top of rice.
Sprinkle Lipton onion soup mix over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 3 hours. Uncover the last 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking soda, cocoa, sugar and nuts.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well by spoon.
Spread in greased 6-cup casserole dish.
Top with brown sugar mixed with cocoa.
Pour boiling water over entire batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Serve hot, warm or cool, with ice cream, if not counting calories.

title: beef continental
directions: Brown steak in a little oil.
Put into a large casserole dish. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours in 325° oven.

title: las vegas carrots
directions: Cook carrots in slightly salted water until tender-crisp. Arrange cooked carrots in a single layer in an oblong baking dish.

title: authentic neapolitan sauce for 30(a crowd pleaser)
directions: In large aluminum saucepan, heat olive oil until hot but not smoking.
Add sausage and garlic cloves; brown on all sides.
(Do not burn garlic.)
Remove sausage and garlic; remove pan from heat.
To the pan, add tomato puree, one can at a time, stirring as you add each.
Add crushed tomatoes, sugar and water; stir vigorously to blend.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place ingredients in layers.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in an 11-inch
iron skillet.
Add brown sugar and spread all over bottom of skillet after sugar is melted.
Cut 3 pineapple slices in half.
Place uncut one in the center of skillet.
Then place halves all around skillet, making it look like a pinwheel.
Then place a cherry in the center of all pineapple.
Next, take pecans (flat side up) and fill in bottom of skillet, center to sides with them.

title: layered salad
directions: In salad bowl or Tupperware, make layers as follows: lettuce, cauliflower, bacon, onion, cheese and mayonnaise.
Chill 24 to 48 hours. Salt and pepper and toss before serving.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, eggs, pineapple and bread.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix everything together, except the cheese and tortillas.
Fry the tortillas in oil, then cut them into quarters.

Line the bottom of a 9 x 18-inch baking pan with half of the tortillas, then half of the mixture, topped by half of the grated cheese. Layer the rest of the tortillas on top of the cheese, followed by the rest of the mixture and the grated cheese.
The oven should be preheated to 350°.
The enchiladas should be covered for 30 minutes, then uncovered and baked for 15 minutes more.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Cut shortening into flour mixture. Beat together the egg and the milk.
Add egg-milk mixture to flour mixture.
Roll out and cut the size of a saucer.
Fill with fruit.
Fold over into half moon and use pastry brush to brush edges with cream.
Seal edges.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Saute onion and pork sausage.
Drain fat.
Mix with chilies. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes in 3-quart casserole.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: banana and pineapple dessert
directions: Buy or prepare graham cracker crust (if you make it, it can be put in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish).
In bowl, beat butter, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
Spread over crumbs in pan.
Beat whipped cream until stiff.
Fold in pineapple and banana.
Spread over butter mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining graham cracker crumbs.
Cover and chill at least 12 hours.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat milk and pudding mix on low speed for 2 minutes or until thickened.
In another bowl, beat cream cheese. Add to pudding and mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into the crusts; sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate until serving. Yield:
2 pies (6 to 8 servings each).

title: hot fruit dessert
directions: Grate orange and lemon rinds into sugar.
Spread fruits layer by layer, including oranges and lemons sliced thin in a baking dish.
Sprinkle each layer with brown sugar mixture and a generous sprinkling of nutmeg.
Heat all until very hot and serve with sour cream.

title: no cholesterol popovers
directions: You will also need nonstick cooking spray.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar. Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Press down with fork before baking. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet. Let cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all of above together.
Bake at 375° in unbaked pie shell for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello well in boiling water.
Then add frozen strawberries.
Keep stirring, when dissolved, add crushed pineapple.
Pour all of this in a glass dish.
Place in refrigerator to set.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine ingredients.
Form in 6 patties and brown on both sides.
Place in baking pan; cover with mushroom soup.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: party sausages
directions: Combine chili sauce and jelly in a slow cooker.
Mix well; add sausages.
Cover; put cooker on medium heat and cook for 3 to 4 hours.
The sauce can be frozen and reused.

title: my sister's cheesecake(prep time: 15 minutes)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Combine graham crackers, butter, 2 tablespoons of sugar; blend well. Press into 9-inch spring-form pan. Beat cream cheese, sugar, beaten eggs, vanilla and cornstarch, just until blended; stir in sour cream. Pour into prepared crust. Bake 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 200° and bake for 45 minutes. Turn the oven off and allow cheesecake to cool with the oven door slightly open for 3 hours. Remove from pan. Serve with fruit of your choice or plain. Serves 12. Enjoy.

title: easy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, using saved juice
and	water,	enough to make up required amount of water. Melt
butter in a 12-inch Dutch oven.
Add brown sugar and pineapple
(including
the rest of the juice).
Pour cake batter over the top of the pineapple.
Bake 50 minutes with 14 coals on the top and 10 coals on the bottom.

title: almond delight
directions: Melt margarine; pour over first 4 ingredients (in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish) and bake about 45 minutes, stirring often. (This burns easily.) Cool. Mix together vanilla pudding and milk. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread the baked mixture evenly in the baking dish (saving about 3/4 cup for topping), then pour pudding mixture over this. Sprinkle the saved baked mixture on top, then refrigerate.

title: monterey chicken
directions: Cut cheese into eight equal sticks.
Split chicken in half. Flatten each piece of chicken to 1/4 inch thickness.
Roll each piece around a piece of cheese and secure with toothpicks.
Dip in eggs, then bread crumbs.
Brown on all sides in margarine. Dissolve bouillon in water.
Thicken and season.
Add mushrooms, pimento and rice.
Place in casserole and arrange chicken on top. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Combine butter, peanut butter and confectioners sugar.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies and walnuts.
Chill.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Chill.
Dip in chocolate.
Melt chocolate bits and chocolate bar.
Dip balls into this using a fork to cover and remove to cookie sheet.
Chill.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Combine zucchini, baking mix, onion, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper, oregano, garlic, oil and eggs.
Pour into a greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. (Reduce temperature 25° if using ovenproof glass dish.)
Let cool and cut into squares.
Serves 6 as a vegetable.

title: bleu cheese and mandarin salad
directions: Blend sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add to remaining ingredients and toss.

title: lemon upside-down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put lemon slices into pan.
Pour half of glaze over lemon slices.
Make cake according to directions. Pour over lemon slices.
Bake until done, about 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes. Turn onto serving dish.
Serve warm with glaze on top of whipped cream.

title: spinach bread dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach in colander; squeeze out all water. Mix mayo, sour cream, soup mix, chopped water chestnuts, onion, salt and pepper.
Chill at least one hour.

title: salmon cheese ball or spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use as a ball or with crackers as a spread.

title: dirt cake
directions: Note:
Need 1 plastic flower pot (10-inch deep, 8-inch round) and 1 bunch silk flowers.

title: healthy pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Beat with mixer at high speed for 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into a 10-inch Bundt pan coated with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. (Test for doneness.
It may need to cook longer.)
Cool upright for at least 30 minutes.
Invert pan; remove cake and serve. Makes 16 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill for at least 3 hours.

title: pineapple applesauce cake
directions: Blend sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs, beating well. Sift dry ingredients together; add to egg-sugar mixture.
Beat well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Bake in large tube pan at 350° for 2 hours.

title: turnips
directions: Peel and slice a quarter inch thick.
Keep in cold water until cooking time.
Place in hot water and cover, lightly salted.
Stew until tender.
When tender, place on a platter and smother with butter.

title: tomato relish
directions: Skin tomatoes, mash down and drain.
Cook down for 10 minutes. Add salt and chopped onions, boil for 2 hours.
Add vinegar and sugar and sweet peppers, boil another 1/2 hour.
Seal in jars.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding mix with vanilla and milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Butter 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place layer of whole graham crackers in dish.
Spread on half of pudding mixture over crackers.
Top with second layer of graham crackers.
Spread remaining half of pudding mix over crackers.
Top with third layer of crackers.
Cover with prepared chocolate frosting.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice cookie dough and arrange on pizza pan.
Press dough together to seal.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or golden brown.
Cool crust.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice to toss bananas in.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together, then spread on cooled crust.
Layer fruit on cheese. Chill and serve.

title: meat loaf italiano
directions: Combine ground	meats, egg, bread crumbs, green pepper, onion, salt, pepper
and
1/2 can herb sauce; mix well.
Shape into
1 large loaf (split loaf in half).
Place cheese slices in
center of	loaf, sealing edges well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes;
drain off fat.
Pour remaining sauce over meat loaf. Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: marinated mushroom salad
directions: In large saucepan, combine oil, vinegar, water, salt, garlic powder and pepper and bring to a boiling point. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Add mushrooms, carrots, green pepper and onion. Cover and simmer 3 minutes. Add pimentos and basil. Chill 1 day before serving.
Makes 5 cups.

title: brenda's taters
directions: Peel potatoes and cut like French fries.
Take heavy duty aluminum foil and cover cookie sheet.
Spray with Pam.
Spread out potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with bacon and chives.
Put butter on in pats.
Cover with foil.
At this time you can bake in a 325° oven approximately 30 minutes or until tender. Or put on your grill while you barbecue.
When done, top with sliced cheese of choice.

title: quiche
directions: Sprinkle grated cheese and crumbled bacon in pie shell.
Mix eggs, whipping cream, milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour over cheese and bacon.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese, onion and eggs together.
Fold broccoli into mixture.
Put into buttered baking dish and dot with butter.
Put crushed white crackers on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar.
Cream until fluffy. Add eggs and bananas.
Mix well.
Sift flour with soda and salt. Stir in nuts.
Bake in loaf pan one hour at 350°.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagna as label directs.
In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot oil, cook broccoli and onions until tender. Remove pan from heat. Stir in Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, salt and egg.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain noodles; place in single layer on wax paper.
Evenly spread cheese mixture on each noodle.
Roll up each noodle, jelly roll fashion.
Into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, spoon about 3/4 of the sauce.
Arrange rolled noodles, seam side down, in sauce. Top with Mozzarella cheese and remaining sauce.
Cover dish loosely with foil.
Bake until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: lime jello salad
directions: When Jell-O is almost set, add the rest of the ingredients and let set.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours before serving.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Roll in flaked coconut.

title: lasagna maria
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, omitting salt and then drain.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble; set aside.
Combine egg and next 5 ingredients, stirring well.
Spread 1/2 cup meat sauce in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Layer half of Ricotta cheese and 1/3 cup remaining meat sauce. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: beth's cherry delight
directions: Spoon pie filling into a 9 x 12 inch pan -- spreading evenly -- then mix the butter and cake mix together to form crumbs.
Spoon crumbs over the top of the pie filling.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes or until top is a very light brown.
So easy and so good -- especially good served warm with ice cream on top.

title: saute vegetables
directions: Saute onions in oil 3 minutes, stirring.
Add carrots, celery, water and soy sauce.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: swiss broccoli soup
directions: Combine dry milk, flour and seasonings in a quart heavy saucepan.
Stir in water and chicken broth until smooth.
Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Meanwhile, saute onion in butter until tender, about 3 minutes.
Stir onion mixture and cooked broccoli into thickened mixture.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in cheese until melted.
If necessary, return to low heat to finish melting cheese.
Do not boil.
Serve immediately.
Very good.
Makes approximately 8 cups.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion; strain fat.
Mix with all remaining ingredients and be careful not to mash beans.
Warm in 300° oven for 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: gumbo pot pies(makes 8 servings.)
directions: Bring chicken, 2 quarts water, quartered onion and bay leaves to a boil in a Dutch oven. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken; reserve 1 1/2 cups broth and discard onion and bay leaves. Let chicken cool. Skin, bone and coarsely chop chicken. Cook flour and oil in Dutch oven over medium heat, stirring constantly, 15 to 20 minutes or until roux is chocolate colored. Add bell pepper, chopped onion and garlic; saute 2 minutes.
