Add okra, tomatoes and green chiles, sausage, thyme and reserved 1 1/2 cups broth. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Beat in eggs.
Add water, spices, soda, baking powder, salt and flour, then add apples or applesauce. Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
This is to be baked in a bread pan. Can also add 1 cup raisins or 1 cup nuts.

title: fried rice
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 cups hot water (I do this in a microwave).
Brown rice in 3/4 stick margarine in Dutch oven.
When rice is brown add onion and carrot, stirring constantly.
Add beef bouillon and stir.
Immediately cover and place in oven.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.
I use a cast iron Dutch oven for this.
The rice comes out really fluffy.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Sift sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Melt margarine and stir well into the dry ingredients.
Add eggs, vanilla and chopped pecans to
mixture.
Pour into unbaked 8 or 9-inch pie shell. Bake 35 minutes in 325° oven.
Cool to room temperature before serving.
May be served topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chocolate marshmallow roll
directions: Pour 1 c. boiling water over 1 stick oleo or butter.
Bring to boil, add 1 c flour and heat 10 minutes.
When cool, add 3 eggs, 1 at a time; beat until light.
Add 1 tsp soda.

title: anthony's awesome chicken and rice
directions: You will need 9 x 13-inch baking dish, small bowl, measuring cup and measuring spoons.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drain all juice off of veggies, when chopped.
If not, the spread will be too juicy.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix all together; pour into pans.
Put in freezer.
Take out 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Chinese noodles.
Just before serving, add Chinese noodles.

title: chinese pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until onion is fully cooked. Drain.
Place in a casserole dish.
Warm up creamed corn.
Then place corn on top of ground beef and onion.
Then top with mashed potatoes.
Put butter or margarine pats on top and place in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: cabbage pudding
directions: Cut cabbage into small pieces and cook in salted water until tender.
Drain and put in casserole dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add sugar, cheese, soup and milk.
Mix in 1 cup of cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of cracker crumbs on top and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° until brown and thickened.

title: venison and mushroom gravy
directions: Spray casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Layer venison, seasonings and soup in 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: baked apples in orange sauce
directions: Peel and slice apples into baking dish.
Toss brown sugar, bread and butter together and sprinkle on top of apples.
Cook juice, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Pour over apples and bread.
Bake in 2-quart baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 15 more minutes.

title: lemon curd coffee cake
directions: Heat sour cream until warm.
Add to the yeast mixture along with the lemon rind and salt.
Beat in 2 eggs and then add enough of the flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on a floured board and knead 6 to 7 minutes until smooth.
Place dough in lightly buttered bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Let rise until double in bulk, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix the juice, Kool-Aid and sugar in a gallon jug.
Finish filling the jug with water.
When you are ready to serve, add the Sprite and sherbet.

title: fried corn
directions: Place bacon and onion in pot; saute.
Place washed greens into pot.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 cup warm water.
Pour over greens.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer. Cooking time varies.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream together and roll into small balls.
Press with a fork. Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil.
Wait until chocolate is dissolved and mixture is thick.
Can keep refrigerated in a jar. When serving, warm up in microwave as needed.

title: delicious cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, mix cheeses, green onions, olives and pimentos.
Add mayonnaise only enough to make spreadable.
Slice French bread, sandwich style and stuff with cheese mixture.
Wrap with foil and place on cookie sheet.
Bake until cheese has completely melted, about 20 minutes.
Slice and enjoy.
This bread goes well with most any meal, especially, spaghetti dinners and barbecues.
"Everyone will love it!"

title: baked bread pudding
directions: Soak the bread in cold water for about 1 hour.
Squeeze out as much of the moisture as possible and mix the bread with currants, raisins, sugar, nutmeg or lemon rind, melted butter, beaten eggs and milk.
Turn into greased pie dish and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° to 350°.

title: relish
directions: Chop onion, celery and eggs together.
Add rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Can be made ahead.
Can not be frozen.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer your salad starting with lettuce, peas, celery, onion and bell pepper.
Fry bacon and crumble over salad.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Top with mild Cheddar cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs until light and foamy.
Add the oil, sugar, grated zucchini and vanilla to the eggs.
In a separate bowl, sift the flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add the dry ingredients to the egg mixture; blend in the chopped nuts. Pour into one large or three small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Cool.
Freezes well.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch round pan.
Add onion, dill weed and garlic.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Shake cut biscuits in Parmesan cheese.
Place on top of butter mixture.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Line casserole dish with mashed potatoes (save 1 cup for top). Add a layer of hot dogs, green beans or peas and cheese.
Pour can of mushroom soup over this and top with remaining mashed potatoes.
(Cheese can be on top, if desired.)
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until hot and bubbly.

title: mama's salad
directions: Slice lettuce and lay on a platter.
Spread on mayonnaise and sprinkle with cheese.
If salad is to be eaten as a dessert, add sliced pears or peaches on top.

title: best ever hot slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cabbage and bring to a boil.
Add cabbage and mix thoroughly.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press rolls into large, greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, dressing and mayonnaise.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle with vegetables, chopped fine.
Top with cheese.
Chill and cut into bars to serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sour cream; mix well. Mix the cranberry sauce and nuts, then add to Jell-O mixture. Pour into a 6-cup mold or dish.
Stir a few times as it sets to keep the cranberries and nuts from settling to the bottom.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, cocoa, flour, eggs, vanilla and nuts. Bake in uncooked pie shell at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until middle is done.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Pour cold vinegar over all.
Let sit 6 weeks in vinegar and spices.
Take out of jar.
Pour in clean pan or sink.
Pack back in jar.
Layer sugar and layer cucumbers.
Let sit 2 weeks.
Ready to eat.
Put spices in bag before putting in cucumbers.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Layer the ingredients in a large flat platter or shallow bowl. Begin with mixture of refried beans and taco seasoning.
Next, spread layer of sour cream.
Add layer of cheese.
Finish by sprinkling with the vegetables.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cranberry relish
directions: In a food grinder or blender, coarsely grind cranberries and orange.
Add sugar and orange liqueur; stir until combined.
Cover and refrigerate at least one hour before serving.
Can be made up to one week ahead and refrigerated.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: judy's jan hagel
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar, then egg yolk and cream well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and pat dough evenly onto a greased 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Brush with egg white diluted with a little water and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 30 minutes. Cut into squares while still warm.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients and onion.
Add small amount of oil.
Mix well; alternate vinegar and oil, ending with oil.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a skillet over medium-high heat, cook garlic in margarine for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp. Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry-sour cream dessert
directions: Oven - 350 degrees.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, nuts, crumbs and margarine.
Mix at low speed, until crumbly.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups for topping.
Press remaining mixture in a 9x13 inch pan. Spread with pie filling.
In small bowl, blend sour cream, egg and nutmeg.
Pour over pie filling and spread.	Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake for 40-50 minutes.
Topping should be golden. Serve warm or cold.
(Refrigerate leftovers.)
Serves 12.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on medium heat until mixture is thick.
Pour in 1 (9-inch) cooked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: tomato pickle relish
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook very slowly for 1 hour, stirring often.

title: brownies
directions: Beat oleo and sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time) and beat well. Add chocolate syrup, then flour, baking powder and vanilla. Spread in 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool before frosting.

title: pimento cheese
directions: If using food processor, put all ingredients in and turn on until all is fine and mixed well.
If not using food processor, grate cheese.
Mash peppers with fork until you have small pieces. Mix all ingredients.

title: champagne dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender (except oil).
Remove blender cap and slowly pour oil into the mixture.
Blend until creamy.
So good.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring gently to mix.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: chicken and gravy
directions: Salt and pepper the fryer to taste.
Brown it in a little bit of oil.
Pour off excess oil and add chopped onion.
Add mushroom soup and water.
Cook until chicken is done and serve over rice.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in Pyrex dish.
Mix flour and sugar with milk.
Pour over butter and stir slightly.
Pour peaches in middle of mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Makes its own crust.)

title: doug's favorite chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in large saucepan and bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool and enjoy!!! Note:
The recipe has to be doubled to get enough to fill Doug!!!

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add jam, raisins and egg yolks; beat until smooth.
Add flour and milk to which soda has been added. Mix well.
Add spices and nutmeats; mix well.
Fold in egg whites which have been stiffly beaten.
Pour in greased layered pans. Bake in a 400° oven until done.

title: bean hot dish
directions: Brown lightly hamburger, onion and bacon.
Mix catsup, brown sugar, dry mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper to taste and add to hamburger.
Add beans, undrained.
Put in casserole and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size chunks.
Peel and cut potatoes, carrots and onions.
Place in a very large pot with water, salt and pepper.
Cook for 10 days at simmer.
Will feed 150 people. If more than 150 people show up for dinner, toss in rabbits.

title: refrigerator coconut cake
directions: Make cake as per directions. After it cools, slice each layer in half (4 pieces).
Mix the next 3 ingredients; using half of this mixture, spread between layers.
Take the other half of mixture and mix with Cool Whip and frost entire cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mom's corn and cottage casserole
directions: Brown onion in 2 tablespoons butter until limp.
Sprinkle corn with flour in a bowl.
Add seasonings, cottage cheese and onion and stir until well blended.
Fold in the eggs.
Turn into a buttered square or oblong casserole.
Sprinkle with corn flakes, then drizzle 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tacos
directions: Brown ground beef until brown.
Add chili powder and garlic to taste.
Add onion and cook for 4 minutes.
Drain grease and add cumin and enchilada sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add cheese and cook until cheese is melted.
Fill shells with meat; add toppings as desired.

title: candied carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water until tender.
Put in shallow casserole.
Put remaining ingredients in a bowl and blend thoroughly.
Spoon mixture over carrots.
Place under broiler and broil 4 to 5 minutes.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth; add remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture in thin layer over flour tortillas; roll up and wrap in foil or wax paper; refrigerate overnight. Slice into small rolls and serve with salsa.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix mashed banana and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and nut meats.
Slowly add milk and mix well.
Pour in greased and floured pan and let stand 20 minutes before baking. Bake about 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Test like cake.

title: zest vegetable medley(microwave)
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, place water, salt, cauliflowerets, broccoli and carrots.
Cover.
Microwave at High 16 to 18 minutes, stirring after 8 minutes.
Drain.
Stir together horseradish, onion, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Pour over drained vegetables and toss gently to coat.
Combine saltine crumbs, margarine and paprika.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top of vegetables.
Microwave at High 1 to 2 minutes, or until hot.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter; cook onion until tender.
Add milk, soup and cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake 30 or 40 minutes at 350°.

title: 21-second candy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to rolling boil and time for 21 seconds. Take off heat and add peanut butter. Fold in cereal and peanuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Cool and store.

title: kentucky fried chicken cole slaw
directions: Be sure that cabbage and carrots are chopped up in very fine pieces (the size of rice kernels).
Combine remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add cabbage and carrots; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.
(It is critical to refrigerate slaw for at least 2 hours before serving.)

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pan and simmer until potatoes are cooked thoroughly.

title: janis' fruit pie
directions: Drain all fruit and cut up oranges and peaches into smaller pieces.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie shells and chill. If desired, sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: "no" bowl chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well the first 5 ingredients with a fork in a large 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Make 3 wells and put into them the vanilla, vinegar and salad oil.
Pour 2 cups water over all and mix with fork.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cereal stuff
directions: Melt butter first, then combine all other ingredients.
Cook at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Makes a great snack.

title: fig preserves cake
directions: Blend together all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring after each one is added.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple caramel rolls(makes 12 rolls.)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 2 teaspoons brown sugar, 2 teaspoons margarine and 3 pecan halves in each of 12 medium muffin cups; place in oven until melted.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados and mix with rest of ingredients until creamy.

title: bread pudding with bourbon sauce
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and pour into a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle top with raisins which have been plumped in bourbon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Top will fall.

title: pumpkin tea bread
directions: Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Dust lightly with flour; tap out any excess.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and pumpkin pie spice into bowl and reserve.
Combine pumpkin and water into small bowl; reserve.
Combine shortening, sugar and eggs into large mixing bowl and beat at high speed 3 minutes.
Stir in dry mixture and pumpkin mixture alternately until batter is smooth.
At this point, add nuts.
Pour into prepared pans and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until inserted wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pans 5 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack and let cool completely before cutting.
Store in plastic bags in or out of refrigeration.

title: pork chop surprise
directions: Put rice in casserole.
Mix and heat soups (canned) and water. Pour this mixture over rice.
Put pork chops on top and sprinkle dried soup on top.
Cover with tin foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Into an ungreased flat cake pan, 8 x 10-inch, or 8 x 8-inch, sift flour, sugar, baking soda and cocoa.
Into this mold of dry ingredients, poke 3 holes.
In one hole, drop vanilla; into another, drop vinegar and in the third, melted shortening.
On top of all this, pour cup of cold water.
Beat together by hand until well blended and bake 35 minutes (more or less) at 350°.

title: peanut soup
directions: Combine celery, onions, butter and flour; add chicken broth. Cook until done.
Add peanut butter, pepper and half and half; cook 10 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with peanuts.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Pour the last 3 ingredients on the chicken.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or 2 to 4 hours before cooking.
Cook on the grill until done.
Baste every 5 to 10 minutes while on grill.

title: mashed potatoes and onion rings
directions: Mix well; put in buttered bowl.
On top, put 1 can French fried onions.
Bake covered 1/2 hour, then uncovered 1/2 hour. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken zings
directions: Break apart chicken wings on first and second joints. (Discard tips or cook with onion, salt and celery for chicken broth.)
Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken in large, shallow dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, on a flat cookie sheet, 10 x 15 x 1-inch, at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender and brown.

title: peppermint fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk. Boil over medium heat for 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add marshmallow cream and vanilla chips and stir. Add peppermint candy and stir. Add a drop or two of red food coloring. Let cool. Refrigerate until firm.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
(Cooking times will not work if oven is not thoroughly heated.)
Cut margarine into cake mix, add water, oil and eggs to mixture with 1/2 can of condensed milk.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a greased and floured long cake pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° (should
not be too gooey or not at all runny). Peel caramels and put in pan with 1/2 can of condensed milk and melt over very low heat.
Stir in the pecans.
Pour mixture over the hot cake.
Add the rest of the cake mix on top of caramel. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl stir together salad dressing, mustard, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add macaroni, celery and onion; toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.

title: nestle butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Melt morsels and butter over hot (not boiling) water.
Remove from heat and put in a large bowl.
Stir in brown sugar.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Beat in eggs and vanilla extract.
Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Wash mushrooms, remove stems and finely chop.
Cook and stir chopped stems and onion for 5 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients and 1 Tbsp. butter.
Fill caps and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: chicken pie superb with sweet potato crust
directions: Clean and disjoint chicken.
Place on rack in container half filled with hot water.
Add carrot, onion, celery, parsley, rosemary, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Partly cover with a lid and simmer for 3 to 4 hours or until tender, turning occasionally. Cool chicken in broth, breast side down.
Skim off excess fat from stock.

title: basic punch recipe
directions: Add the ginger ale when ready to serve.
Could use an ice ring or a container of sherbet.
One and one-half of this recipe will almost fill the Pine Grove Church punch bowl.

title: glazed raisin-cinnamon biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Vanilla Glaze, until dough forms. Beat 20 strokes.
Turn onto board dusted with baking mix.
Gently roll to coat; shape into ball and knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut with 2 1/2-inch cutter dipped in baking mix. Bake on greased cookie sheet until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Spread with Vanilla Glaze while warm.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Beat butter until smooth and creamy.
Beat in sugar gradually until fluffy.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla extract.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating 3 minutes after each addition. Spread filling in pie shell.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Spread whipped topping over chilled filling.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over pie.
Serve chilled.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in boiling water.
When cool and ready to eat, beat until foamy.
Add cottage cheese and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into mold or pan and refrigerate.

title: beef stroganoff(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; trim fat from meat.
Rub both sides with garlic.
Pound flour into meat.
Cut meat in 1 1/2 x 1-inch strips.
In hot butter, in Dutch oven, brown meat, turning often.
Add onion, saute until golden brown.
Add water, stir to dissolve brown bits in bottom of pan.
Add soup, mushrooms.
Cook uncovered over low heat, stirring occasionally until mixture is thick and meat is tender.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream. Heat but do not boil.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: no peeky
directions: In a bowl, mix together rice and chicken soup.
Spread into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or roaster.
Place washed and drained chicken pieces on rice mixture. Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Cover tightly.
Place in a preheated 350° oven for 2 hours and "No Peeky" until done.

title: black magic cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt into mixing bowl.
Add eggs, oil, coffee, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool on a rack.

title: helen's black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix salad oil, vinegar and 1 tablespoon sugar in jar.
Shake well.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 48 hours.
Stir after 24 hours.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: southern style black-eyed peas
directions: Place ham hock in water; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.
Add peas to ham.
Continue simmering 1 1/2 hours; add rice and simmer 45 minutes or until rice and peas are done and liquid is almost absorbed.
Remove meat from bone; serve peas and rice on platter.
Place ham on top.

title: meatball heroes
directions: In a saucepan, heat together 2 tablespoons of cooking oil and garlic.
Stir in soup mix, water, tomato sauce, sugar and oregano. Gently boil sauce, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally until slightly thickened.

title: party rye pizzas
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Pour off grease.
Add cheese to the meat to melt.
Add spices.
Spread on party rye bread.
Warm in 350° oven to serve.
These can be made and frozen for future use.
Freeze them first on cookie sheets, then transfer into bags. Makes 45 to 50 sandwiches.

title: best fried okra
directions: Wash, drain and cut okra in 3/4-inch pieces, discarding end pieces.
Wet okra in buttermilk covering each piece.
Toss okra in meal until each piece is coated.
Drop in hot oil deep enough to float okra.
Cook on medium heat until brown.
Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with salt.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Combine tomatoes, brown sugar and salt with 1/4 cup boiling water in saucepan; boil for 5 minutes.
Place bread crumbs in casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over bread crumbs.
Add tomatoes.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all other ingredients in with the broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes (until cheese is melted).
Remove from oven and stir.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: prune bran muffins
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor and mix 1 minute. Grease mini muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Will make 35 miniature muffins.

title: exotic spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package and drain well.
Add sour cream, onion soup and wine.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle breadcrumbs over top if desired. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(May be reheated, covered with foil.)

title: chicken pilaf
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients, except chicken, margarine and seasonings.
Brush chicken breasts with margarine.
Season with pepper and paprika after placing chicken on top of rice.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: beet salad mold
directions: Drain beets and save liquid.
Measure, adding enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Bring liquid to a boil.
Remove from heat; add jello, sugar, vinegar and horseradish.
Stir until dissolved.
Add beets and pour into 1-quart mold; chill.

title: herb toast
directions: Spread slices of bread with softened butter and quarter diagonally.
Place on cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, dried basil and sesame seed.
Bake 1/2 hour at 250°.
Turn oven off, but leave bread in oven overnight or several hours.
Keeps months in airtight containers.

title: irene's refrigerator rolls
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients with beater.
Add eggs and yeast cakes dissolved in warm water.
Beat until smooth.
Grease bowl and top of dough.
Cover with damp cloth.
Keeps 3 days.
Let rise 1 1/2 times.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring first four ingredients to a bubbling boil, stirring all the time.
When bubbles appear all over the top, boil and stir over medium heat 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter; stir until well mixed.
Pour into 9-inch greased square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: green tomato jelly
directions: Boil tomatoes and 4 cups sugar 10 minutes.
Add Sure-Jell and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Pour into clean glass jars and let set for 24 hours, then cover with wax.

title: butterscotch rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan well.
Place 1 package frozen dinner rolls in Bundt pan.
Mix ingredients together and pour over rolls.
Let rise.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meat balls
directions: Saute onions until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and mix well.
Shape
into 2 ounce round meat balls.
Makes 8 to 10 meat balls
per
pound.
Place in a greased baking pan and bake in a hot
oven at 400° until brown all over, about 30 to 40 minutes. Remove
the
meat balls from the pan and empty the grease. Replace the meat in the baking pan and cover with the tomato sauce.
Cook in
oven
at 325° for another 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: pecan breaded chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and lightly grease a baking pan.
Flatten chicken breasts with a meat pounder and lightly pepper them.
Melt butter in a saucepan and then remove from heat.
Whisk in 1/4 cup mustard.
Dip chicken into butter and mustard mixture and then into ground pecans.
Arrange chicken breasts in the baking pan.
Place chicken in the oven and bake for 20 minutes until golden brown. Remove chicken from pan.
Pour pan drippings into a bowl; add sour cream and mustard mixture on each dinner plate and cover with a chicken breast.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook oil, sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Cool. Cook macaroni according to package and blanch with cold water. Add any or all of the following:
celery, tomatoes, mushrooms, black olives, cauliflower, radishes, carrots, pepper and cucumber.

title: shrimp scampi 2
directions: Saute garlic in butter in heavy skillet for a few minutes. Add shrimp and saute for 4 to 5 minutes or until shrimp are done.

title: candy apples
directions: You will need 8 wooden sticks.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Combine sausage, celery and onion in large skillet.
Saute mixture over medium heat until sausage is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain well.
Pour sausage mixture into large bowl. Add cornbread, bread crumbs, poultry seasoning, pepper and chicken broth in order listed; blend well.
Stuff mixture into bird or bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: bread sticks
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Stir in shortening, sugar, salt and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat well.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Beat well.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Divide dough into four parts.
Roll out one part on a floured surface into an 8-inch square.
Cut into four 2-inch strips.
Roll along 8-inch side to form sticks.
Place on greased baking sheet. Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with salt (or sesame or caraway).
Repeat with remaining dough.
Let rise until light, 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: sweet and sour tofu
directions: Slice tofu into 1-inch squares that are about 1/4-inch thick. Lightly brush a cookie sheet with oil.
Place the tofu squares on the sheet and brush the tops with remaining oil.
Broil for 5 minutes on each side.
Steam the carrots and green pepper slices until tender.
Combine the cornstarch with 3 tablespoons of the tamari.
Mix thoroughly to remove all lumps.
In a large saucepan, combine the pineapple juice, brown sugar, vinegar, garlic powder, cornstarch mixture and the remaining tamari.
Bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer until thickened.
Add the steamed vegetables, pineapple and tofu.
Serve on rice.

title: fettuccine with spinach-ricotta sauce
directions: Heat oil (medium heat).
Add onion and garlic.
Cook 2 minutes. Stir in flour.
Cook 1 minute.
Gradually whisk in milk.
Cook until sauce is smooth and bubbly.
Stir constantly.
Mix in spinach, Ricotta, 1/3 cup Parmesan, sun-dried tomatoes, basil and nutmeg.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until heated through.
Serve over cooked fettuccine and garnish with scallions and pine nuts, if desired.
Sprinkle with freshly ground black pepper and pass extra Parmesan.
Serves 4.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in saucepan and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper and let stand until cold.
Flatten with a glass, if desired.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and spoon into a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with topping and bake 25 minutes (or until bubbling and heated) in a 350° oven.

title: instant hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients until blended well.
Keep this dry mixture in a tightly covered jar.
To make the cocoa, place 1/2 cup of the mix in a cup and fill with hot water.
Stir until mix dissolves.
Will make 12 cups cocoa.

title: cajun gumbo
directions: Brown chicken and sausage in oil.
Drain and set aside.
Over medium heat, stir flour and butter until well mixed.
Add all vegetables except okra and cook until tender.
Add water, tomatoes, tomato paste, spices, chicken and sausage.
Simmer over low heat for approximately 2 hours, adding more water, if necessary.
Add shrimp and okra and cook through.
Serve over rice.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add cottage cheese, cream and mayonnaise.
Blend well.
Add carrots, green pepper and onion.

title: rock salt beef(beef with a crust)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Season meat with pepper.
Insert meat thermometer into thick part of roast.
Mix salt, flour and water. Make mixture thick that just clings together.
Put on 1 1/2-inches thick in oiled roasting pan.
Be sure it is well covered (no cracks or holes, especially around base).

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In skillet, brown onions first, then add ground beef, salt and pepper.
Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add Worcestershire sauce and let simmer about 3 minutes, then pour in tomato sauce. Let simmer on low heat about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: butterscotch snack cake
directions: In a large saucepan, combine pudding mix and milk.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat; stir in dry cake mix.
Pour into greased 13x9 baking pan. Sprinkle with butterscotch chips and nuts.
Bake at 350 for 35-40 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.

title: homemade custard ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and milk.
Cook in top of double boiler over simmering water, stirring, until slightly thickened.
Cover and cook 10 minutes more on low heat.
Add hot milk mixture slowly to eggs, beating constantly.
Return mixture to top of double boiler and cook over boiling water 5 minutes or until custard coats spoon.
Cool.
Add vanilla, sweetened condensed milk and whipping cream.
Add evaporated milk last and stir well.
Freeze in electric freezer.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Set 1 dozen aside for decorations.
Crush others with sugar to make a syrup.
Dip each ladyfinger in syrup and line bottom and sides of pan or mold with them.
Fill the mold in layers:
strawberries, cream and ladyfingers.
Put in refrigerator for 1/2 day.
Turn out of the mold.
Decorate with whipped cream and strawberry halves.

title: cheezy snacks
directions: Put cheese spread on crackers.
Top with grapes or cherries.

title: sausage balls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In a large bowl, mix sausage, cheese, milk and egg.
Mix well.
Slowly add biscuit mix, onion soup mix and pepper.
Mix well.
Form into balls; place on cookie sheet and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Serve warm with a spicy mustard dip.

title: plantation rice
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Take cover off and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice to dissolve gelatin.
Let cool and add rest of ingredients.
Let stand; refrigerate until real firm.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt 1 cube butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, Bisquick and milk.
Stir a little of the melted margarine into the batter. Return to pan, reserving 1 cup.
Top with plenty of sugared berries.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Top with reserved 1 cup batter. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda; let stand while you mix the rest.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten egg.
Add date mixture and vanilla.
Then add flour and nuts.
Bake in moderate oven about 45 minutes.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins. When done, peel skin off and cut potatoes into cubes. Fry bacon until crisp. Crumble onto potatoes. Add green onions, celery seed, salt and pepper. Add mayonnaise. Stir until mixed together. Potatoes will still be chunky.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Mix together with all other ingredients and pour into medium size casserole dish. Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream sugar with shortening.
Beat in egg and lemon extract. Stir in carrots and raisins, then sifted dry ingredients.
Roll in 1-inch balls; flatten with back of spoon.
Put on baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: beef loaf
directions: Mix and spread in pan or make into loaf. Decorate top with more catsup, if desired. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked fish
directions: Spray a large baking dish with cooking spray or line with foil.
Place fillets in dish.
Slice peppers into thin strips. Sprinkle fish with garlic powder, salt and paprika.
Put equal amount of the red and yellow pepper on each fillet.
Drizzle Ranch dressing over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until fish flakes with a fork.

title: wiener wraps
directions: Measure oil into measuring cup; add milk to fill to 2/3 cup. Add mustard and onion; stir into Bisquick to make soft dough. Turn onto lightly floured board; roll out and cut into 10 strips. Roll each strip around wiener and place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Brush with butter and bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serve hot with mustard.

title: kelly's double-decker fudge
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar, Marshmallow Creme, evaporated milk, butter and salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils.
Boil gently, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes.
Divide mixture in half.
To one half (about 3 cups), add chocolate pieces and stir until melted and blended.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: mix up perfect pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Place in covered container and store in refrigerator.
Mixture will keep for a month and will make 7 (9-inch) shells.

title: jiffy orange nut bread
directions: Grease a large loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure flour, soda, baking powder and salt into sifter.
Set aside.
Melt butter in boiling water in medium-size bowl.
Blend in orange rind and juice, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Stir until flour is damp.
Will be lumpy.
Pour batter into greased pan.
Place walnut halves on top.
Bake 30 minutes or until wooden toothpick in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan; cool on wire rack.

title: turkey mole(mole de guajolote)
directions: Skin the turkey leg; cover it with water; add onion (peeled and quartered), coriander and bay leaves.
Simmer for at least an hour, until meat comes easily off the bone.
Drain the turkey and reserve the broth.
Rub the onions, bay leaves and coriander through a sieve and add the juices to the broth.
Brown the roux a bit and add the warm broth.
Heat and stir until mixture thickens.
Add the chocolate and allow it to melt completely in sauce, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in raisins.
Chop the chipotle or jalapeno and stir into sauce.
Now add the turkey in pieces not more than 1 inch square.
Sprinkle seed on top, stir in wine and garlic put through garlic press.
Return to heat and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Serve with brown rice, yellow squash and tortilla.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs and vanilla. Mix flour, salt and cocoa together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Dissolve baking soda in vinegar.
Fold into batter.
Add food coloring.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when placed in the middle of cake.

title: flower garden cake
directions: Beat 6 egg whites stiff; add pinch of salt and 3/4 cup sugar together.
Set aside.
Beat yolks, 3/4 cup sugar, 1/2 cup lemon juice and lemon rind.
(Soak unflavored gelatin in 3 tablespoons cold water and set aside.)
Cook yolk mixture until it is bubbly and coats the spoon.
Add gelatin; fold in egg white mixture while still very warm.
Pour over torn pieces of angel food cake in alternate layers in angel food cake pan; refrigerate overnight. Frost with whipped cream.
This recipe should be doubled if using large angel food cake.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients together.
Mix well the eggs, milk and oil.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with the apple slices.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix together hamburger, garlic powder, Italian seasoning and salt and pepper.
Roll thin; cut in squares.
Roll in flour.
Brown both sides.
Put in baking dish.
Pour over mango, onion, mushrooms, can of cream of mushroom soup and alternate with meat. Bake at 350° until mixture bubbles awhile.

title: ting a lings
directions: Melt chocolate chips and Hershey bars.
When melted, add corn flakes and cocktail nuts.
Melt well and drop by 1/2 teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: flaky pastry
directions: Sift the flour into a medium-sized bowl.
Cut in shortening with 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
(Add the sugar now, if desired.)
Using a fork, stir in water, a tablespoon at a time, until dough forms a ball.
Too much water or overmixing will make the crust tough.

title: lane cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add milk alternately with creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in the mixture.
Bake at 325° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 layers.

title: sheila's chicken
directions: Roll chicken in
flour; dip chicken in salt and pepper; fry and remove.
Add rest of ingredients, stirring constantly. Place chicken in casserole.
Pour sauce over it.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer.

title: mex-tex dip
directions: Layer on round platter:
refried beans, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, onions, tomatoes and olives and cheese.

title: overnight salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges, reserve juice. put juices in sauce pan with lemon juice and water. Stir in pudding mix and cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Remove from heat and cool. Add pineapple, oranges and marshmallow. Fold in whip topping. Chill overnight. Just before serving fold in bananas.

title: brownies
directions: Bake at 350° until done.

title: overnight chili
directions: Pour beans, tomatoes, beef, pepper and onion and add spices. Make sure you layer the mixture as it is directed.
Stir up and cover and cook over low heat for 10 to 12 hours or 5 to 6 hours in crock-pot.

title: mock stuffed peppers
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion and pepper and saute.
Add ground beef. Stir until beef is done. Add stewed tomatoes, rice and salt. Add 2 cups boiling water and stir. When it starts boiling again, lower heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Put aside for 5 minutes before taking the cover off.

title: copper pennies
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in 4-quart pan.
Add onions and pepper.
Saute until golden brown.
Sprinkle flour and stir until absorbed into onions.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly with wooden spoon. Remove from heat.
Gradually add broth, stirring constantly.
Add water and bay leaf.
Return to heat; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low; cook uncovered 30 to 40 minutes. Discard bay leaf.

title: good morning muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, bran, wheat germ, oats, cornmeal, sugar, walnuts, raisins, baking powder and soda, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg in a large bowl.
Combine buttermilk, butter, apple and egg.
Mix until combined.
Pour and bake.

title: portuguese red bean soup
directions: Wash beans and cover with water.
Add ham hock and sausage (I substitute kielbasa) and cook on low heat 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Add other ingredients.
Let come to a boil, then simmer for 1 hour or so (until potatoes are tender).

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook shrimp and remove shells.
Place butter in frying pan. When melted, add diced green pepper, diced onions and garlic salt. Saute.
Add can of tomatoes and cooked shrimp.
Cook for approximately 20 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice, toast or noodles.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix margarine, powdered sugar and eggs.
Beat for 15 minutes. Smooth over crust.
Spread pineapple over top of powdered sugar mixture.
Layer sliced bananas, then Cool Whip.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over top of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with cherries and chopped nuts.

title: southern pralines
directions: Place graham crackers close together on a cookie sheet.
Boil remaining ingredients together for 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Watch carefully so it doesn't burn.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: rosy cinnamon apples
directions: Dissolve candy in boiling water in saucepan.
Then add the apples which have been pared and cored.
Cook slowly until tender when pierced with a fork, turning frequently.
Remove apples to a shallow dish, then add the sugar to the cinnamon syrup and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over apples, turning them carefully to glaze each. Cool and serve as a garnish for meat.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups, milk and dressing together to create gravy. Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and put 2/3 of gravy in pan.
Sprinkle rice and seasoning packet over mixture.
Place chicken on top and pour rest of gravy over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: southern ham and bean soup
directions: Trim fat from ham hocks and parboil for 20 minutes. Discard water. Wash and sort navy beans. Add beans to ham hocks; fill pot one-half full with water.

title: chocolate sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and chocolate.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Mix until smooth.
(May have to add more flour to rolling consistency.)
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Roll dough out on floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, cheese and sour cream.
Add egg, corn, buttermilk and Crisco.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes or until brown.
Makes 1 large skillet.

title: punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat peanut butter and cream cheese at medium speed.
Mix sugar and Cool Whip.
Freeze for 8 hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs with fork; beat in milk, with fork, to egg mixture. Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add corn to mixture.
Dot butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes in a buttered dish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon until crisp. Crumble. Saute onion in margarine. Mix bacon, onion, squash, salt, pepper and cheese. Spoon into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake until browned. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add ingredients as listed.
Blend with mixer. Add nuts last.
Grease and flour pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar and let set overnight or at least a few hours.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and whipped topping. Chill thoroughly.
Keeps very well.
May also be frozen.

title: buffalo turkey wings(makes 4 servings)
directions: Cut off wing tips; reserve for other use.
Cut wings into 2 pieces at joint.
Combine flour, salt and cayenne pepper on a plate.
Dust wings in flour mixture, shaking off excess.
Heat 1 1/2-inches of oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add wings in single layer and fry for 10 minutes, turning once, until browned. Drain on paper towels.
Repeat with remaining wings.

title: 57 sauce cheddar burgers
directions: Combine first ingredients.
Form into 5 patties.
Grill or broil to desired degree of doneness.
Serve in sandwich buns. Makes 5 servings.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place chicken in mixing bowl. Add Lipton soup mix, whole can of cranberries and French dressing. Mix all well and pour into glass baking dish. Bake at 350° until done, bubbly. Serve over rice.

title: date loaf bread
directions: Soak dates in the boiling water.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Recipe can be doubled with good results.

title: mrs. hinkle's halloween popcorn balls
directions: Mix molasses, brown sugar, water and vinegar in a pan.
Bring to a boil (soft ball).
Stir in butter.
Add popped corn and mold into balls.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.
Will keep months in the refrigerator.

title: pork tenderloin wrap ups
directions: Cut pork in two inch sections. Slice onion and tomatoes. Cut peppers into quarters. Take two slices of bacon and make an

X. Place a slice of pork in center and sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper. Place green pepper, slice of onion and tomato on top. Pull up bacon slices and secure with a toothpick down the center. Place wrap ups on grill over coals and cover grill. Bake for 1 hour, when done, put slice of cheese on wrap ups and close grill for 30 seconds.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Select ripe tomatoes of uniform size.
Wash; cut in half-inch slices.
Dip in bread crumbs, then in eggs, then in bread crumbs. Fry until done.

title: frosted apricot jewels
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt; cut in butter and cream cheese until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add coconut and preserves, mixing well.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Spread each cookie with frosting and top with a pecan half.
Yield:
about 4 dozen cookies.

title: chicken stroganoff(serves 2 to 3)
directions: Cut each chicken breast crosswise into 10 or 12 strips.
Melt margarine or butter over moderately high heat in 12-inch skillet. Add chicken and sprinkle with salt.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the onion, mushrooms and paprika.
Cook 2 minutes longer, continuing to stir.
Add the water.
Reduce heat to medium. Cover and cook an additional 2 minutes.

title: rita's chicken vegetable soup
directions: Using Fresh Chicken:
In large Dutch oven or stock pot, boil chicken in 3.5-quarts slightly salted water.
Remove chicken from broth and cut in pieces.

title: dream pie
directions: Prepare and bake crusts.
Drain fruit and set aside.
Heat juices and stir in sugar and flour.
Cook until clear and slightly thickened.
Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Cool slightly and add fruit and nuts.
Pour into pie shells and refrigerate overnight.
Top with one small container of Cool Whip.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Place breasts in a 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch dish for baking.
Mix remaining ingredients and cover chicken.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: peach custard cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour over cake.	Bake 30 minutes.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Use an oblong casserole dish and put layer of chicken.
Cover layer with cream of celery soup, then pour Veg-All on top of this. Add mushroom soup and chicken soup.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a criss-cross on each cookie with fork prongs that have been dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden. Cool on cookie sheet for about 1 minute, then remove to rack to finish cooling.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen 2 1/2 inch cookies.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer a thick layer of lettuce, then a thin layer of cucumbers, purple onions, cauliflower, radishes, carrots and boiled eggs.

title: club day chicken and dressing
directions: Mix stuffing, margarine and water.
Place 1/2 mixture in buttered 12 x 8-inch dish or pan.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, mayonnaise and salt; spread over stuffing.
Top with other half. Mix eggs and milk and pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or a few hours.

title: gooey cake
directions: Spread on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice dinner
directions: Trim fat off chops and pepper.
Coat skillet with cooking spray.
Over medium heat, add chops and cook until brown on both sides.
Remove chops and drain on paper towel.
Wipe pan drippings from skillet.
Coat skillet with additional cooking spray.
Add onion and green pepper and saute until tender.
Stir in rice, tomatoes, water, salt and mustard, then add pork chops.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix together lightly; shape into cakes and fry.

title: cream soda biscuits
directions: Fill med. size bowl 3/4 full with flour.
Make a `well' in the middle of the flour and add oil.
Slowly add the pop.
While you are adding the soda, slowly stir in flour from the edges until you have a soft ball of dough.
It is much like you are making homemade egg noodles.
There should be flour left on edges of the bowl. Place some of the left over flour on a flat surface and knead gently a couple of times.

(Do not over knead the dough.) With the flat of your hand or a rolling pin, flatten dough until it is 1/2 to 3/4 in. thick, depending on how thick you like your biscuits. With a biscuit cutter, drinking glass or whatever you can find when camping, cut biscuits out.
Pour a small amount of oil, I like olive oil, into the bottom of a Dutch oven or baking sheet.
Place biscuit dough in pan and then turn them over so there is oil on both sides of dough.
Bake for approx. 15 - 20 min. at 350° or in a Dutch oven.

title: irish trifle
directions: Line glass dish with 1 package of ladyfingers or pound cake. Put all ingredients in blender.
Pour into bowl.
Top with whipped cream.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor and mix. Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: lime salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar and boiling water.
Let this cool, then beat in electric mixer until very foamy, then fold in pineapple, marshmallows, nuts, cottage cheese, lemon juice and whipped cream. Pour into bowl and refrigerate.

title: beef - nine layer dip
directions: Layer in order given in 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oven beef burgundy
directions: In Dutch oven combine beef, soup mix, mushroom soup, wine, garlic and pepper.
Add Kitchen Bouquet (for color).
Cover and cook in a 300° oven for 2 hours.
Add onion and carrots and cook 1 hour more.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix all together.
Spray frypan with Pam.
Roll meat into 35 to 38 balls and put in pan.
Spoon 1 can French onion soup (Campbell's) over balls (use soup full strength).
Then spoon a can of chicken gumbo soup over meatballs (full strength).
Heat at about 250° for approximately 1 hour.

title: sally's 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Beat egg well.
Add butter, oil and other ingredients until mixed well.
Bake well for 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: smoked oyster frittata
directions: Dice the oysters.
Remove the seeds from the tomato and dice. Add spinach to egg mixture.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet. Add spinach mix and green onions.
Sprinkle oysters evenly over spinach mix. Top with cheese.
Cook over low heat until set. Top with tomato and onion tops. Serves 1.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and pumpkin pie spice; blend well. Blend in pumpkin.
Add evaporated milk and blend well. Pour into pie shells.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat and continue baking for 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: cocoons
directions: Mix together.
Roll in finger lengths in palm of hand.
Bake until lightly browned on bottom, about 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar and egg. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in alternately with milk.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Immediately roll in melted butter, then in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Makes 12 medium puffs.

title: summer pie
directions: Mix together and put in pie crust.
Refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Mash bananas.
Add eggs and banana to sugar mixture. Add dry ingredients. Mix well.
Add walnuts. Pour into a floured pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Let frozen pie crust thaw slightly.
Prick all over with fork and bake according to package directions.
In a double boiler, stir together butter, cornstarch, cocoa, sugar and half the milk.
Heat mixture and slowly stir in the rest of the milk until well blended. Bring to a boil stirring often and boil for 1 minute.
Beat egg yolks lightly in a small bowl.
Stir some of the hot mixture into the yolks and add the yolks to the double boiler.
It's important to add some of the hot mixture into yolks before hand, so they won't curdle.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: yogurt dressing
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover; chill.
Yields 1 cup.

title: baked cream cheese
directions: Unroll dough on lightly floured surface; press seams together to form a 12 x 4-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle cheese with dill weed. Place cheese dill side down in center of dough.
Wrap dough around cheese.
Seal edges.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Brush with egg yolk.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Serve with crackers or apple slices.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Do not use a mixer with this cake.
Very little mixing is required.
Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in vanilla, 1 cup pecans, pineapple and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 wax paper lined 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove to rack and cool completely.
Fill and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix above ingredients and shape into a ball. Chill.
Roll in chopped parsley or crushed nuts as you desire.

title: hamburger tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
In small bowl, mix soup with 1/2 cup water to thin.
In 9 x 9-inch pan, layer half hamburger, half mixed vegetables and top with Tater Tots.
Pour over half soup mixture. Layer remaining ingredients again, topping with soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Put in a large bowl and cream the shortening, sugars and peanut butter.
Add milk, egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in flour and baking soda.

title: nutter butter popcorn
directions: Microwave popcorn using package directions.
Bring sugar and corn syrup to a rolling boil in saucepan; remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla. Pour over hot popcorn in bowl.
Mix to coat well.
Store in airtight container.

title: john's spiced nuts
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
In a heavy 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, cook sugar, water, syrup, salt, allspice and cinnamon until mixture boils.
Stir occasionally.
Cook to firm, soft ball stage (235°) on a candy thermometer.
Take off heat.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Stir until mixture begins to thicken and gets lighter in color.
Pour into prepared jelly roll pan.
Working quickly with 2 forks, separate nut halves, each one from the other.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: veal with scallops
directions: Cut veal into 2-inch pieces, dredge in flour, shake off excess flour.
Brown in two tablespoons olive oil, remove from pan.
Add peppers and mushrooms to pan and cook until tender.
Add scallops and cook until tender.
Remove from pan.
Add chicken broth and simmer for one minute.
Add veal, peppers, mushrooms and scallops and simmer until veal is tender.
Add wine and cook one minute more.
Serve with cooked noodles or rice.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, brown sugar, pudding mix and vanilla together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add dry ingredients (flour and baking soda) and mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: company turkey loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: micro-magic cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms by gently twisting them.
Place caps, open side up, on microwave-safe plate; set aside.
Chop stems.
Combine stems and butter in a 1-quart casserole. Microwave on High, uncovered, for 2 to 3 minutes or until tender. Add cheese mix until softened and creamy.
Stir in garlic salt and pepper sauce.
Spread cheese mixture on top.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 2 to 3 minutes or until mushrooms are heated through.
Sprinkle with paprika and/or parsley flakes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: In bowl, mix Eagle Brand milk, Pet milk, pudding and sugar. Pour into 4-gallon ice cream freezer; add milk until mixture reaches the fill line.

title: pepper steak
directions: The amount of steak, tenderizer, salt and pepper depends on your judgement.

title: chirico and peppers
directions: Slice and peel chirico. Fry in pan until brown. Add 1 1/2 cups water. Add chopped/sliced green peppers and chopped onion. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until water is almost gone. Add Ragu traditional sauce. Simmer 15 more minutes.

title: wonderful pound cake
directions: Stir the shortening to soften.
Gradually add sugar and cream together until light and fluffy.
Beat about 3 minutes on medium speed.
Add lemon peel and juice.
Add milk and mix enough to break up creamed mixture.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture and mix until smooth (about 2 minutes on low speed).
Scrape sides of bowl often.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 1 minute after each (low speed).
Beat additional 1 minute at end.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often.

title: strawberry delights
directions: *You can get these from Kroger's in the deli; some call them cream horns.
It is a round pastry filled with cream.

title: corn-crisped chicken
directions: Mix cornflakes crumbs with salt and pepper.
Line shallow baking pan with aluminum foil.
Dip chicken pieces in evaporated milk, then roll immediately in seasoned corn flake crumbs.

title: mary anne's slush
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in container of an electric blender.
Add enough ice cubes to measure 3 cups.
Blend to desired consistency.

title: bourbon dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook overnight on low heat in a crock-pot.

title: salmon with dill dip
directions: Mix in blender or food processor and serve as a mold with crackers or on cucumbers.

title: susan's seven layer cookies
directions: While oven is preheating, melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan in oven (watch carefully and remove pan when butter is melted). Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over melted butter, patting lightly for even layer.
Sprinkle coconut over crumbs.
Sprinkle butterscotch and chocolate bits evenly over coconut.
Drizzle can of milk and pat lightly to set nuts into milk.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cookies will be browned.
Cool.
Cut into 1-inch bars.
Store airtight.

title: famie's favorite buttercream icing
directions: Pour sugar in a medium size mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients except water.
Add about half the water and mix.
Add remaining water, a little at a time, as you mix.
When done it should be thick and creamy.
Put a spoon in and pull out, the peak formed by pulling spoon out should hold its shape.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and put into a greased bread pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a moderate oven.
You may use a package of onion soup mix on top, if desired.

title: apple bars
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; set aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Make a ball and roll in remaining nuts on wax paper.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll in pecans.

title: angel food supreme
directions: Remove cooled cake from pan and slice in 3 horizontal layers. Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water. Add frozen berries (do not thaw). When berries have melted, add ice cream, a bit softened, 1/3 pint at a time. Beat well with rotary beater.
Put a small amount of jello mixture in bottom of empty angel food pan, then a layer of cake.
Repeat until all mixture and cake are used. Set in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Remove from pan and frost with sweetened whipped cream.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in heavy saucepan the milk, oleo, salt, sugar and cocoa. Bring to a boil.
Boil hard for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: homemade egg substitute
directions: In a small bowl combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Use as a substitute for one egg.
One serving equals 1 1/2 meat, 90 calories, 127 mg sodium, 1 mg protein and 5 g fat.

title: mama lib's shower punch
directions: Boil water.
Dissolve jello and sugar in the boiling water. Add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Cool and add the ginger ale when you pour the mixture into the punch bowl.
Serves 20 adults or 10 thirsty children!

title: jiffy peach cobbler
directions: Mix first four ingredients into thin batter.
Melt butter or oleo in baking dish.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Add peaches over batter.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: meat ball appetizers
directions: Make small meat balls from ground chuck.
Simmer in a covered skillet (low heat) until done.
Put the grape jelly and chili sauce in a saucepan and simmer.
When sauce is well mixed, put meat balls in sauce and simmer a few minutes.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together (beat eggs first) all other ingredients except Cheddar cheese.
Pour batter over melted oleo.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until brown.
Good with anything.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain pears and save liquid.
Mix 1 cup of pear juice with lemon Jell-O.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Set aside.

title: fruit salad
directions: Empty pie filling into bowl. Cut up peach slices as necessary. Add drained pineapple and oranges. Add grapes. Add bananas just before serving. Mix.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Layer bread, cheese and bacon; beat rest of ingredients together and pour over top.
Put mushrooms on top.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: cream butterscotch scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly butter cookie sheet.

Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt in a large bowl. Work in the butter with your fingers or pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal. Add the beaten eggs, vanilla and cream. Stir until blended. Turn out onto lightly floured board. Knead for a minute. Pat or roll dough about 3/4-inch thick.
Cut into wedges.
Place on cookie sheet and bake about 15 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in boiling water 5 minutes; drain. Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots.
Fold in squash and onions.
Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread half stuffing in bottom of loaf pan.
Spoon in vegetable mix over stuffing, then cover with rest of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl combine flour and cocoa; set aside.

In a large mixing bowl, beat the butter or margarine with an electric mixer on medium to high speed about 30 seconds or until softened. Add sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Beat until well combined.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Gradually beat in the flour mixture.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press down center of each ball with thumb.
Drain maraschino cherries, reserving juice.
Place a cherry in the center of each cookie. In a small saucepan, combine the chocolate pieces and sweetened condensed milk; heat until chocolate is melted.
Stir in 4 teaspoons of the reserved cherry juice.
Spoon about one teaspoon of the frosting over each cherry, spreading to cover cherry. (Frosting may be thinned with additional cherry juice, if necessary.)
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes or until done.
Remove to wire rack; cool.
Cover and store at room temperature up to two days.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Combine 1/4 cup peanut butter with the pudding mix and milk in a saucepan.
Bring just to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cover.

title: blitz kuchen(german coffee cake)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Pour into greased pan.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Lightly spray pie plate or square pan.
In bowl, mix cooked spaghetti, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Next goes sour cream and a couple of slices of Mozzarella cheese.
Pour spaghetti sauce and top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.

title: frozen fruit cream
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves (about 2 minutes).
Pour into a large bowl.
Add orange juice and lemon juice; set aside.
Beat cream cheese at high speed with a mixer until creamy.
Gradually stir about 1/4 juice mixture into cream cheese.
Add to remaining juice mixture, stirring constantly.
Fold in whipped cream and almond extract.
Pour mixture into freezer container of a 1-gallon hand-turned or electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Pack freezer with ice and rock salt; let stand 1 hour.
Serve with fresh plum sauce. Yields 3 quarts.

title: the best dressing
directions: Mix Italian dressing mix, vinegar and water together. Add olive oil and mix well.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Break lettuce and cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Layer lettuce, cauliflower, onion rings, bacon pieces and salad seasonings, making several layers of each.
Seal with Miracle Whip on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: easy walnut fudge
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Cover with English walnuts.
Combine Eagle Brand milk, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips. Melt over low heat.
Pour over walnuts.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Beat until smooth.
Use to dip thick apple slices in.

title: quick fruit crisps
directions: Put fruit filling in ovenproof dish, about 2-inches deep. Layer cake mix lightly on top (do not sift or break up lumps). Poke with fork in several places to allow some mix into the filling. Layer again with cake mix. Drizzle melted butter over cake mix. Try not to puddle butter. You may add more cake mix and butter until desired crust thickness. Bake for 10 minutes at 400°. Broil for 2 minutes or until crust browns slightly.

title: deluxe coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to instructions.
Fold in 1/2 cup shredded coconut.
Bake in a loaf pan.
While still warm, punch holes in cake with a table knife.

title: french onion soup
directions: Pour bouillon or stock in crock-pot.
Cook onions slowly in butter for 15 minutes in large covered skillet; stir occasionally. Uncover and add salt, sugar, flour and vermouth.
Stir well.
Add to stock in crock-pot, cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours, on high for 3 hours.

title: pierogi(polish dumplings)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all the ingredients and knead into a soft, pliable dough.
Cut in half and let rest, covered, for 10 minutes.
Roll out each half thinly.
Using a drinking glass, cut the dough in round circles.
Place less than a tablespoon of filling in the center of each circle.
Rub the edges with a little bit of water and fold over.
Gently press out excess air and seal into a half moon.
(You may freeze pierogis at this point for future cooking.)
Cook in boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes.
This recipe makes 70 to 80 pierogis.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients with a spoon.
Grease cookie sheet and line with greased wax paper.
Spread batter (will be thin).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or less.
Sprinkle kitchen towel with powdered sugar.
Turn cookie sheet over on towel.
Peel off wax paper.
Roll in towel and let cool for 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla, margarine and powdered sugar.
Spread over bread. Roll up and refrigerate.

title: kahlua chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until done. Take from oven.
Poke holes in warm cake.
Pour a mixture of 6 tablespoons Kahlua and 1 cup powdered sugar together on warm cake. Let it soak in.
Invert on cake plate.
Can be topped with a chocolate glaze if desired.

title: my favorite chocolate cake
directions: Put all in bowl and mix well.
Grease and flour loaf pan or 2 layer pans.
Pour batter into pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until cake tester comes out clean.
Great with Peanut Butter Icing.

title: creamed hamburger
directions: Fry hamburger.
Mix together milk, soup, salt, pepper, cheese, butter, flour and egg.
Heat a little, then add water and broth. Heat until thick.
Serve on bread.

title: easy macaroni salad
directions: Boil, rinse, drain and cool macaroni.
Add eggs, carrots, celery and onion to macaroni.
Toss to mix.
Stir in mayonnaise. Season with salt and pepper.
Chill overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning to hamburger.
Mix well and cool.
Shred lettuce; add chopped tomatoes, onion and grated cheese.
Add hamburger to that mixture. Just before serving add corn chips and salad dressing.
Very good!

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat 6 egg yolks with mixer until very thick and lemon colored, about 5 minutes.
Beat sugar in gradually.
Beat in cold water, lemon extract and grated lemon.
Beat in flour.
Beat separately 6 egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and salt and beat until stiff enough to form peaks.
Gently fold into batter with spoon.
Pour batter into ungreased deep 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Invert pan immediately; let cake hang in pan until cold.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Top with ketchup and cheese.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Put flour in a large mixing bowl.
Make a well in the flour and add the eggs and salt.
Now add the very cold water (small amounts at a time) until consistency is workable.
Roll out on floured surface; let dough dry, then cut into strips.
Cook in boiling broth about 20 minutes.

title: doughnut muffins
directions: Stir flour mixture into shortening mixture alternately with 1/2 cup milk.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Roll immediately in 6 tablespoons melted butter, then in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Serve hot.

title: fall apple dip
directions: Blend together first 4 ingredients.
Wash and slice apples; dip in orange juice.
Drain and arrange in concentric circles on a pretty plate; can place dip in the center in a bowl.
Sprinkle additional chopped peanuts on top of dip.
Delicious!

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients thoroughly.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of mixture for topping. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt oleo over low heat.
Let cool and add sugar, molasses and egg.
Mix.
Sift flour, soda, spices and salt and add to first mixture.
Form into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars. Add eggs and mix until well blended.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash beans in cold water, drain and add 6 cups of cold water. Bring to a boil slowly.
In a hot skillet, combine 4 tablespoons olive oil, onion, bell pepper, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add kielbasa and brown.
Add skillet mixture to beans and cook over low heat until beans are tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Serves 6 with rice.

title: mexican dish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Microwave until hot (very hot). Spread top with sour cream and rest of cheese.
Put remaining Fritos around dish.
Microwave until cheese is melted.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, powder and sugar.
Combine the juice and rind of one orange, butter and enough hot water to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Add egg and mix.
Run cold water over berries that have been cut in half to remove seeds.
Drain well.

title: kaffree tea
directions: Boil water in pot.
After boiling, take off fire and add tea bags.
Let cool before adding apple juice and lemon-lime.
Chill and serve.

title: yummy yams
directions: Combine all, except pecans.
Pour into a greased, 2 1/2-quart casseorle.
Arrange pecans around the edge.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: quiche
directions: Cook ground meat, onion and pepper.
Add a little salt, then drain.
Mix meat and all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Cook at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chop chicken in small pieces, combine with finely chopped celery.
Add Miracle Whip until it is well coated, probably about 1 cup.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie* * * * *
directions: Oysters Parmesan is my favorite entree from Trader Vic's and this is as close as I have come to duplicating it.
They also serve them with caper butter.

title: party potatoes
directions: Pare and boil potatoes in salted water until tender.
Mash with the next five ingredients and place in a buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Blend 1/3 cup sugar with cornstarch.
Add pineapple.
Cook, stirring constantly, until it is thick and clear.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Add eggs gradually. Blend in milk and vanilla.
Spread cooled pineapple mixture over bottom of shell (uncooked).
Pour in cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce to 325°.
Cook for 50 more minutes.
Cool.

title: no cook icing
directions: Mix at low speed until well mixed, then at high speed for 5 or 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix pumpkin pie mix with eggs and pour on top of the yellow cake mix, then pour boiling water on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Mix margarine, milk and white sugar; boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
