Add peanut butter, marshmallow and vanilla; mix thoroughly, then add Quaker oats.
Stir good.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.

title: aunt ella's chocolate cake
directions: Mix together baking soda and baking powder.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar gradually, then alternate flour and milk.
Add cocoa.
Beat! Add oil, coffee and vanilla.
Beat!
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured, for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: slush
directions: Put in freezer (best in 2 separate containers).
Allow expansion room.
Leave in freezer 18 to 24 hours before time to use.
Break with fork and press with something.
Can add soda after set, if desired.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together pumpkin, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and fold into batter.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack.
A moist bread, freezes well.

title: fried shrimp batter
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dip peeled shrimp into mixture and deep fry.
Mixture coats approximately 3 to 4 pounds of medium shrimp.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain the asparagus.
Put melted butter in casserole dish, then the cut-up asparagus.
Sprinkle with pimento, then layer with eggs, cut into rings.
Pour undiluted soup over the top.
Sprinkle top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: garden club chicken salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets into small pieces and peel stems, discarding any woody pieces.
Finely chop broccoli flowerets and stems together with remaining ingredients.
Season and refrigerate overnight.
Serve on lettuce or with croissants.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.

title: caramel pudding(karamelpudding)
directions: Place 1/2 cup sugar in a heavy skillet over medium heat.
With wooden spoon, keep sugar moving constantly in skillet until sugar is completely melted and of a rich medium brown color.
Pour into a baking dish and quickly tilt sides of dish until bottom is evenly coated.
Set aside.
Scald cream.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup of the milk in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently until smooth. Set aside.
Mix remaining milk, cake mix and margarine in a large bowl.
Press 1/2 of the cake mix into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup of the walnuts and 1/2 cup of the chips over crust; top with caramel mixture, spreading to edges of pan.
Top with teaspoonfuls of remaining cake mixture; press gently into caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup walnuts and 1/2 cup chips.
Bake 18 minutes. Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 24.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk. Stir slowly for 1 minute. Fold in Cool Whip and frost cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: seafood paella
directions: With brush, scrub mussels and clams under running water. Remove beards from mussels.
In 8-quart Dutch oven over high heat, in 1 inch boiling water, heat mussels and clams to boiling. Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook until shells open.
Discard top shell from each mussel.
Rinse mussels on half shell and clams in cooking broth.
Cover and refrigerate mussels and clams. Reserve 2 cups clear broth.

title: thousand island blender dressing
directions: Add all ingredients together in blender.
Blend until smooth. Pour over your favorite salad.
Serves 8.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix butter in hot rice and then add to other ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: beef tortellini appetizers
directions: * Tortellini are usually found in the frozen foods section by the pizzas, egg rolls, etc.

title: pecan caramel clusters
directions: Line three 15 X 16 inch baking pans with wax paper. In large heavy saucepan over low heat, cook and stir the peanut butter and chocolate chips until melted.
Remove from heat, stir in cheerios, M&M's, and pecans until coated.
Drop by rounded Tbsp. onto prepare pan and refrigerate for 4 hours or until firm.

title: southern comfort punch
directions: Mix in large punch bowl, add ice and enjoy!

title: 14 layer chocolate cake
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar. Add eggs.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients.
Beat well. Spray cake pans.
Put 4 tablespoons of batter in each pan. Cook at 325° just until they are done. Do not overcook.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sour cream.
Add dressing mix, lemon juice and shrimp.
Chill before serving.

title: squash puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls into deep fat and fry.

title: turkey divan
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and place in casserole dish with turkey. Combine mayonnaise, juice, curry powder and soup. Pour over meat and broccoli. Melt butter; stir in crumbs and spread on top of casserole with the cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 4 to 5.

title: special chocolate dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer the ingredients.
Swirl hot fudge topping and freeze.

title: grandma anna kline's lemon pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, butter, flour and lemon rind and juice.
Add to boiling milk.
Cool.
Beat egg whites and fold into cooled custard mixture.
Pour into prepared pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Then bake at 325° until custard is set.

title: seven layer bars
directions: In 9 x 10-inch pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle on cracker crumbs evenly and pat down, then put in a layer of chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour condensed milk over evenly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Allow to settle for 3 to 4 hours before cutting.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown beef or sausage with onion.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomato paste, salt, pepper, garlic powder, parsley, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan.
Mix brown sugar and pudding mix. Sprinkle over rolls. Mix cinnamon and sugar. Sprinkle over pudding mix, then add pecans.
Pour melted butter over pecans.
Place on counter overnight (8 to 10 hours). Do not cover.
The next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let set 10 minutes.
Turn out on plate and eat.

title: glogg
directions: *Bruise in a mortar with a pestle or by covering with a towel and crushing with a rolling pin.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat the eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, spices, vanilla and milk.
Add margarine to mashed sweet potatoes and blend with milk and egg mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes more or until firm.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together and pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until filling is set.

title: pie crusts(5 crusts)
directions: Mix shortening and flour.
Add other ingredients. Do not knead.
Roll out dough into circles and put in tins.
Trim edges. Puncture with fork.
Bake 2 and freeze rest.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: Butter baking dish and put in apples.
Mix together the sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add egg and mix until crumbly.
Pour onto apples.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve plain or with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, nectar, oil, eggs and extract together. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Cool 10 minutes in pan, then remove to a plate.
While cake is warm, mix powdered sugar and lemon juice until well blended.
Pour over warm cake.
Cool completely before serving.

title: rhonda's holiday ribbon pie
directions: Stir chocolate with water over low heat until melted; cool. Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add chocolate.
Fold in 3 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Spoon in 1/2 mixture into pie shell. Sprinkle with filling, pressing down firmly.
Spread remaining chocolate mixture carefully over filling.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip if desired.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown the sausage and ground beef.
Mix all of the ingredients together in crock-pot.
Let cook until cheese is completely melted.

title: turtle cake
directions: Fix the cake according to box directions.
Bake half the cake mixture in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt the caramels, evaporated milk and margarine over low heat.
Pour the caramel mixture, the pecans and the chocolate chips over cake, then pour rest of cake mix over caramel mixture.
Bake 25 minutes more.

title: stew
directions: Fry meat in skillet.
Put all other ingredients in crock-pot until hot.

title: pizza chicken
directions: Place Shake 'n Bake and oregano in the shaker bag.
Shake to blend.
Prepare, coat and bake chicken as directed on package. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese has melted.
Do not spoon pan drippings over chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spaghetti primavera with cheese sauce
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed.
In skillet over medium-high heat, cook garlic in oil until lightly browned.
Discard garlic. Add broccoli and red pepper; cook, stirring constantly, until coated with oil.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook until broccoli is tender-crisp, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to low.
Add cheese spread, milk, Parmesan cheese and oregano; cook until cheese melts and mixture is blended.

title: date logs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a medium bowl.
Stir in dates, walnuts and eggs into flour mixture.
Spread evenly into a greased pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until light brown.
A slight dent is left when lightly touched.
Cool on a wire rack.
Cut into logs and roll in confectioner s sugar.

title: italian beef
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer slowly for 3 hours or until tender.
Cool and store with juice overnight.
Remove fat.
Slice very thinly.
Heat juices and beef.
Serve on hard rolls for sandwiches.

title: brisket
directions: Lay brisket on large piece of heavy-duty tinfoil.
Sprinkle brisket with tenderizer, pepper, liquid smoke, onion soup mix, garlic powder, 1/2 cup barbecue sauce.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Add raspberries to Jell-O and boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients; set aside until firm.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together and spread on a large tray or dish.
Top with any or all:
sliced mushrooms, green peppers, onions, tomatoes, and always end with shredded lettuce and grated cheese.

title: cherry dessert
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, put the pie filling.
Pour cake mix on top. Pour melted butter over evenly.
Use a knife to randomly mix through.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ranch dinner
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Add corn.
Heat mushroom soup, milk and broken pieces of cheese until cheese melts.
Add to meat and corn mixture.
Stir in cooked noodles and heat through and serve.

title: cherry-nut ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt; blend well.
Add evaporated milk, milk and vanilla.
Stir in pecans and cherries.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 5-quart hand-turned or electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Allow ice cream to ripen at least 1 hour.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: grandma's easy brownies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream the shortening and melted chocolate.
Add sifted dry ingredients, then add the sugar, eggs, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Pour cottage cheese in bowl.
Add orange jello; mix well. Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Add to cottage cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill at least 1 hour in refrigerator.
May add chopped walnuts if desired.

title: cranberry-nut bread
directions: Grate rind of orange.
Squeeze juice and add enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Add the grated rind and butter. Stir to melt the butter.
In another bowl, beat egg and sugar. Stir into orange mixture.
Add cranberries and walnuts.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to cranberry mixture.
Spoon into buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: garden patch house dressing
directions: In a food processor, place the garlic, sugar, mustard, salt and sour cream.
Add the vinegar.
Blend on continuous speed.
In a thin stream, slowly add oil.
When blended, fold in the parsley and pepper.
Makes 2 1/2 cups of dressing.

title: chicken breast with basil sauce
directions: Bone, split and skin chicken.
Place in skillet with wine, cover and cook over medium heat until done (approximately 10 to 12 minutes).
Remove from heat; set aside.
In separate bowl, whisk yolks, cream, salt, 1/4 cup cooking liquid, parsley and basil. Pour into small saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice.
Place chicken in serving dish.
Pour sauce over before serving.

title: franzenkung(a german potato dish served with roast beef and gravy)
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Place a portion of the cubed potatoes in a blender (do not overfill blender).
Fill blender with water to nearly cover potatoes.
Blend until grated (mixture is watery). Pour mixture into a mesh wire strainer (do not use a colander) and drain off water.
Place strained potatoes in mixing bowl and repeat process until all potatoes are grated.
Add flour, cream and salt to grated potatoes and mix thoroughly; set aside.

title: chess cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add sugars and vanilla; blend well.
Add eggs one at a time and blend well between each addition.
Add flour and mix. Stir in nuts.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes.
Turn onto wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool thoroughly and cut into squares.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round pans, 9 x 1 1/2-inch or rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
In large mixer bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla; beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer; stir in coconut, nuts and boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes for round pans, 35 to 40 minutes for rectangular pan or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool cake 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Frost with Coconut Frosting.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and season to taste; make into balls.

title: cube steak
directions: Sprinkle onion soup over steak after putting in Pyrex dish. Add mushrooms.
Pour gravy over steak with water.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours, covered with foil.
Good for leaving in oven on Sunday!

title: butter-pecan ice cream
directions: Cook pecans in butter for 5 minutes on low heat.
Let cool and drain on paper towel. Mix with rest of ingredients and freeze.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk. Sift together dry ingredients except oats; add to creamed mixture. Beat until smooth.
Add oats and raisins; mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: brownies a 'la cooper
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan. (Don't overbake.)
Cool in pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost with chocolate butter frosting.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; fry hamburger, onion and green pepper together. Layer ingredients into baking dish.
Place half of macaroni on bottom, then hamburger, puree (heated) and cheese (in that order). Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Add pudding to pineapple.
Add Cool Whip, then fruit.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine all together. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in tube or bundt pan.

title: four cheese lasagna
directions: In a large bowl, combine Ricotta, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, eggs and parsley; set aside. In a large rectangular pan, soak uncooked lasagna noodles in cold water for 10 minutes. Drain. Cook hamburger. In large bowl, place spaghetti sauce and stir in cooked meat.

title: poor man's dumplings
directions: Pour in water; mix in center of flour.
Get into soft ball and roll out on dough board.
Cut into squares, rolled thin.
Drop into hot beef or chicken broth.
Use chunks of meat and cook on stove until it boils and dumplings are done.
Very good.

title: yum-yum candied sweet potatoes (yams)
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes about 1/2-inch thick.
Cover sweet potatoes with water; boil until almost tender when pricked with fork.
Drain.
Place in baking dish.
Mix sugars, water, butter and pecans and cook over low heat until slightly thickened. Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stack cake
directions: For the first layer combine flour and butter; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar. Layer on crust.
Mix pudding and milk; place on cream cheese layer.
Cover with additional Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: cucumber cocktail
directions: Sprinkle cucumber with sugar, salt, pepper and lemon juice. Fold cucumber mixture into sour cream.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Serve in lettuce cups or sherbet glasses lined with heart of leaves.
Garnish with thin slices of radish and a sprig of parsley.

title: tea cakes
directions: Put Crisco in microwave for 1 minute.
Beat eggs and mix with Crisco and sugar.
Mix well.
Add flour and mix until it forms a stiff dough.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Press down with a cold fork.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: grey's brown rice casserole
directions: Brown rice in pan on top of stove in butter; do not burn. Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Put rice in casserole dish.
Mix 1 can regular onion soup and consomme; rinse out both cans with water and pour in casserole dish.
Put in a 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve hot.
This is a delicious dish to serve with any kind of meat.

title: toffee squares
directions: Mix margarine and packed brown sugar.
Add egg yolks, flour and vanilla.
Blend well.
Spread dough 1/8-inch thick in cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt 1 large chocolate bar (Nestle or Hershey and spread over cookies when taken from oven. Sprinkle finely chopped nuts.
Cut while warm.

title: country skillet
directions: Empty hash browns into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Drizzle with butter and cook for 35 minutes at 425°.

title: raspberry vodka martini
directions: Fill cocktail shaker with ice.
Add the Framboise and the vodka.
Shake and stir.
Pour into 4 glasses and garnish with fresh raspberries.

title: mom rohrbach's banana nut cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder together.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with combined sour milk, banana pulp and vanilla.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake in a greased and lightly floured loaf or tube pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Check with a toothpick. (High altitude, add 2 tablespoons flour.)

title: steak casserole
directions: Cut steak (any kind) in strips and brown.
Put in casserole dish.
Slice onion in bottom.
Then add meat, potatoes, carrots and celery.
You can cut vegetables any way you want. Then add mushroom soup and add water.
Mix.
Put Reynolds Wrap over dish. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese roll
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Grate Cheddar cheese and combine with cream cheese.
Add onion powder and garlic powder; mix with hands until well blended.
Add chopped nuts. Shape into rolls about six-inches long; sprinkle cayenne pepper over rolls.
Roll in waxed paper and store in refrigerator for a few hours before serving.

title: refrigerator hot peppers
directions: Use warm water.
Add spices, then add cold vinegar.
Cool and add peppers.

title: veggie wedgie
directions: Roll crescent rolls out flat and bake at 325° for 7 minutes. Cool.
Top with cream cheese mixed with mayonnaise and Hidden Valley Ranch.
Top with broccoli, onion, black olives, green olives, tomato and celery.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cut into wedges.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Melt margarine. Add flour and pecans. Press in bottom of pan and cook for 25 to 30 minutes at 325° until light brown. Let cool.

title: bumble bee bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Drop into well-greased tube pan. Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, butter and pecans in a saucepan. Heat and bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan before removing.

title: crazy crunch
directions: Mix popped corn and nuts on cookie sheet or large shallow pan. Combine sugar, margarine and Karo in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture turns light caramel color.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popped corn and nuts.
Mix to coat well.
Spread to dry. Break apart, store in tightly covered container.

title: new lettuce with sour cream dressing
directions: Soak the lettuce briefly in water to remove all the sand. Place in colander and shake out excess water; wrap in a tea towel jelly-roll fashion and place the rolled towel in the refrigerator for 2 hours.
The lettuce will become very crisp.
Combine the remaining ingredients, except the green onions, in a small bowl; blend.
Place the chopped green onions on the bottom of a large bowl; top with the lettuce.
Pour over the cold dressing and toss lightly.
Chill until serving time.

title: spiced french toast
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a shallow dish, stirring well. Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray and place over medium heat until hot.
Dip bread slices, 1 at a time, into egg mixture, coating well.
Place 2 bread slices in skillet and cook 4 minutes on each side or until browned.
Repeat procedure with remaining 2 bread slices.
Sprinkle powdered sugar evenly over toast.
Makes 4 servings.

title: new mexican chili potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in boiling water to cover and cook for 20 to 25 minutes over medium heat, until tender.
Drain and discard water. Put roasted, peeled chilies and garlic in food processor for 15 to 20 seconds, until minced.
Add potatoes, milk, paprika, salt and cayenne pepper.
Process until smooth.
Sprinkle with chives or parsley.
Serves 4.

title: mixed vegetable pickles
directions: Boil this together 10 minutes; add vegetables.
Boil 10 minutes longer.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: sausage or turkey bake
directions: Brown sausage.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put bread in bottom of pan, then add sausage or turkey.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard.
(If using turkey, use sage, 1/2 to 3/4 teaspoon, instead of mustard.) Pour over bread and sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, pour on mushroom soup mixed with 1/2 cup of milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together, except the fruit and then stir in the fruit by hand.
Pour and spread into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fudge nut upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter and stir in brown sugar and pecans.
Put in bottom of a greased 9-inch round cake pan.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add unbeaten egg yolk.
Sift together cocoa, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with a mixture of milk and vanilla.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Fold in egg white.
Pour on top of sugar and pecan mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn out on cake plate while hot.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: mexican deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise. Remove yolks and set whites aside.
Mash yolks with fork.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except olive slices.
Refill whites.
Garnish with olive slices.

title: chicken and apricots
directions: In large nonstick skillet, combine chicken, onion and wine or water; mix in apricot preserves, cover and cook over medium-low heat for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until chicken is done.
Garnish and serve.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together Jell-O and pudding mixes, add 2 cups boiling water.
Let stand until jelled.
Add strawberries.
Add whipped topping.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cube zucchini; cook in salted water for 15 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
In a skillet, melt margarine; add onion and saute. Add cream of mushroom soup, sour cream, 1/2 Stove Top stuffing mix and zucchini; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish; top with remaining stuffing crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Whip together.
Spread over cake evenly and roll the cake up like a jelly roll as tight as you can.
Wrap in tin foil and refrigerate.
Makes one roll.

title: fresh cranberry casserole
directions: Combine sugars, oatmeal, flour and cinnamon.
Add fruit and nuts; mix well.
Spread into casserole and top with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in skillet until clear. Layer chicken and uncooked spaghetti over vegetables.
Add mixture of soup, broth, salt and pepper.
Top with layers of mushrooms and Parmesan cheese.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until spaghetti is tender, stirring occasionally. Yields 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pineapple and cherries in a cake pan.
Pour cake mix from the box over the mixture.
Add the tablespoon of butter over the dry cake.
Bake for 30 minutes or until top of cake is brown.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Combine all
ingredients.
If hard to beat up, add more soda pop.
Makes 50 (4 ounce) servings.

title: texas squares
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil; stir and remove from heat.
In a mixer, have ready the flour, salt and sugar.
Pour hot mixture over dry ingredients; beat on medium for 2 minutes.
Add the sour cream, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Beat all for 1 minute. Pour into a greased 17 x 11-inch cookie pan.
Mixture will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in ice cream freezer until it is frozen.

title: shrimp rice salad
directions: With clean hands, mix together by squeezing with your hands like kneading.
The more you knead, the better the slaw.
Let sit in the refrigerator in a tightly covered bowl for at least 6 hours before using.
This will keep in refrigerator for up to a week, if tightly covered.
Do not store in metal container!

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: Combine brown sugar, oil, egg, vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Stir in rhubarb, nuts and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to rhubarb mixture.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins.

title: dad scott's impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Pour into 9 or 10-inch greased pie pan (grease rim also).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Crust will be on bottom, custard in the middle and coconut, if used, on top.

title: hamburgs italiano
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except buns.
Open buns.
Divide mixture between the 6 opened buns.
Broil 5 inches from the broiler.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread hash browns in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a separate bowl, melt butter.
Add soup, onion, cheese and sour cream.
Stir together and pour over hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers in quarters lengthwise.
Dissolve salt in boiling water.
Pour over cucumbers in crock.
Weight down with a plate.
Let stand for 1 week.
Drain and add 1 gallon fresh boiling water and alum to pickles.
Let stand for 24 hours. Drain.
Make syrup of vinegar, sugar and allspice.
Heat to boiling.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers in crock.
Let stand for 3 days.
Pack pickles in jars.
Reheat syrup to boiling. Boil 10 minutes and pour over pickles.
Seal at once.

title: jo brown's banana bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas. Mix.
Gradually add baking soda, flour and chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: rock cornish hens, garden style
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Rinse hens well, pat dry with paper towels and season inside and outside with salt and pepper.
Place hens in large skillet and brush with melted butter.
Cook in oven 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: In 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine pork cubes, pineapple chunks, bell pepper, celery, mushrooms and onion rings; toss to combine.
In small bowl, combine pineapple juice, vinegar, cornstarch, soy sauce and salt, stirring to dissolve cornstarch.
Pour over pork mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 10 minutes, stirring once or twice during cooking, until thoroughly heated.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Cooking time may be different in your microwave oven. To help ensure good results, be sure to check for doneness while cooking.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Beat over chopped ice until thick.

title: lazy apple pie
directions: Place apples in shallow baking dish.
Thoroughly mix sugar, flour and butter.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in moderate oven (325°) until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream for a taste-tempting treat.

title: tostada casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Mix well.
Line casserole dish with 2 cups corn chips. Spoon meat mixture over chips.
Combine rest of sauce with refried beans.
Spread over meat.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and 1/2 cup corn chips.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, making three layers. Bake as directed. Mix coconut, sugar and sour cream. Reserve one cup of mixture for later. Spread between layers. Add Cool Whip with the cup of the coconut mixture that you saved. Spread on top and sides of cake. Cover tightly and store in refrigerator for 3 days before serving.

title: salad surprise
directions: Drain gooseberries reserving syrup. Add water to syrup to make 1 3/4 cups. Heat 1 cup syrup mixture to boil. Add gelatin and sugar. Stir to dissolve. Add remaining syrup mixture and orange juice. Chill until partially set. Stir in berries, celery and nuts.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Heat orange juice to boiling.
Add jello and cool.
Add applesauce.
Stir well and chill until firm.
Yields 3 cups.

title: microwaving hot mulled cider
directions: In 2-quart capacity container, mix all ingredients.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes or until mixture boils.
Stir.
Strain into mugs.
Garnish with additional orange slices and cinnamon sticks. Yields 4 cups.

title: peach crisp cake
directions: *Can be found in the refrigerated department in stores.

title: scampi a la "fireman chief"
directions: Rinse prawns and set aside.
Heat butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic 1 to 2 minutes or until softened but not brown.
Add prawns, green onions, wine and lemon juice; cook until prawns turn pink and firm, 1 to 2 minutes each side.
Do not overcook.

title: four minute cookies(no bake)
directions: Mix together oleo, sugar and cocoa, then add milk.
Bring to boil in saucepan for 1 minute.
(Mix in pan.)
Add quickly, vanilla and peanut butter.
Add oatmeal all at once and stir well to combine mixture.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: paradise salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple; place on stove and thicken with the following:
flour, sugar, beaten egg and water, mixed well (set aside).
Cut pineapple up fine; cut marshmallows with scissors.
Add hot mixture to pineapple and marshmallows; stir good.
This can be prepared night before.
Just before serving, add whipped cream.

title: "gertie's cookies"
directions: Add water to raisins and boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Stir in soda and let stand.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla, eggs and cooled raisins with the liquid.
Then add flour sifted with baking powder and salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in nuts and drop on baking sheet by teaspoonful.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 425° oven.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Slice cooked carrots while warm.
Add to the remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Will keep for weeks. Recipe can be halved.

title: zucchini toss
directions: Toss all ingredients and serve.

title: cheddar parmesan potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add the salt, Cheddar cheese and Parmesan and Romano blend.
Stir until cheeses melt.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Brown beef, onions and garlic.
Add mushrooms and spices. Cook spinach until very dry.
Strain or squeeze water out.
Mix with soup and sour cream.
Add meat.
Mix well.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8, freezes well.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and well beaten eggs.
Dissolve soda in hot water.
Add nuts.
Add 1 cup of flour, then add bananas, remaining flour and salt.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: date cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Can be frosted with powdered sugar icing or your favorite icing.

title: sugar-free pineapple pie
directions: Drain most of juice off of the pineapple. Mix well sour cream, pudding and cream cheese. Add 1/4 of Cool Whip in mixture. Add pineapple and a little juice in mixture. Mix well and pour in a "baked" deep-dish pie shell. Top with Cool Whip.

title: pudding topper
directions: Melt butter; add coconut and saute until golden brown.
Stir constantly.
Serve on Jell-O pudding.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop up tomatoes (use blender; with small tomatoes, do not peel) and mix with the salt.
Let stand overnight.
In morning, drain off and discard the juice.
Add cabbage and vinegar in large saucepan with tomatoes.
Boil 1/2 hour, then add the onion, green pepper and pimiento.
Add sugar, celery and mustard seed.
Put the cinnamon and cloves in a cheesecloth bag and add to pan.
Cook until the onion is tender.
Remove the cheesecloth bag and add to pan.
Cook until the onion is tender.
Remove the cheesecloth bag. Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal at once.
Makes 7 or 8 pints, depending on how much cabbage used.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; then add next 2. Mix well.
Put in greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: charlotte's mom's strawberry cake
directions: Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13 Pyrex pan or 3 greased round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 45 or 30 minutes respectfully or until done.

title: spinach-bacon deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Scoop out yolks into a small mixing bowl and mash with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon yolk mixture into egg white halves.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cherry whipped cream parfait
directions: Whip whipping cream with sugar, vanilla, and salt.
Fold in sour cream.
Alternate layers of cherry pie filling and whipped cream mixture in parfait glasses.
Chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pizza lasagna
directions: In a 12 x 18-inch baking dish, spread 1/4 sauce, 1/2 Ricotta, 1/3 each green pepper, pepperoni, mushrooms and Mozzarella. Repeat. Top with remaining noodles, sauce, green pepper, pepperoni and mushrooms.
Reserve remaining Mozzarella.
Cover dish with plastic wrap. Shield short ends of dish with 2-inch wide strips of smooth foil.
On microwave cooking rack, cook on High 8 minutes. Discard foil.
Cook, uncovered, 2 to 4 minutes until hot.
Top with remaining Mozzarella.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple cream cheese log
directions: In large bowl combine cream cheese, pineapple, apricots and cinnamon; blend well.
Refrigerate mixture 30 minutes or until easy to handle.
Form into two 7 x 1 1/2-inch logs.
Roll each in chopped pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap; refrigerate until firm. Serve with crackers.
Logs can be frozen.
Wrap tightly and freeze no longer than 3 months.

title: corn pone
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then blend eggs in.
Mix dry ingrdients together.
Pour milk and flavoring (if used) into rest of ingredients.
Bake in lightly greased pan, or muffin tin.
Bake 450° until golden brown.
Insert toothpick into center to test if done.

title: sourdough starter(chuckwagon grub)
directions: You will need a ceramic crock with lid.
Put water in crock; add yeast and sugar to soften.
Stir in flour.
Cover with a clean cloth (or lid).
Let rise until mixture is light and slightly aged (about 2 days).
Mixture will thin as it stands; add flour as needed.
As you use sourdough from the crock, replace it with equal amounts of flour and water.
A staple of every chuckwagon cook.

title: *cheese bread
directions: Add flour, yeast, salt and water.
Knead about 10 minutes. Let rest about 15 minutes.
Butter bottom of a roasting pan. Place dough and spread to size of pan.
Press in cheese cubes and butter top. Cover and let rise until double in size, about 1 hour. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Slice onions into thin rings.
In large pot saute onions in margarine until limp.
Pour half of the onions into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, cover with 1/2 the cheese and 1/2 the crackers. Repeat.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream
ingredients together.
Add one (1 pound 4 ounce) can crushed pineapple.	Stir soft bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake
in buttered casserole at 375°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and puree in blender.
Set aside. Mix chicken, cream cheese and onion.
Season with salt, pepper and cumin.
Spread chicken mix in tortillas and roll.
Lay in baking dish and top with sour cream mixture and Jack cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil last 5 minutes. Makes 12.

title: scallop corn
directions: Do not drain corn.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Puffs up and gets crusty on top.

title: john's margaritas
directions: Fill blender with ice and add ingredients.

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat sugar, salad oil and vinegar to a boil.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: bean salad
directions: On a large platter or individual dishes, arrange greens. Combine remaining ingredients and arrange bean mixture.
Drizzle dressing over entire platter.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese; add celery, onions, seasonings, red pepper and lemon juice.
Mash shrimp and add to cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for several hours.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Add soup and cream cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
I add about 3/4 can water. This makes up fast in microwave.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in cooking dish.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: wild duck and oyster gumbo
directions: Make a roux by heating oil and adding flour.
Blend well and cook until very brown, stirring constantly so it will not scorch. Add onions and cook until tender.
Season duck well.
Fry duck in roux until oil comes out around the edges.
Add warm water and cook slowly for about 2 hours, until duck is tender.
Add oysters about 20 minutes before serving.
Sprinkle with parsley and onions about the same time.
Serve over rice.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Sift all but milk.
Add milk unsifted.
Put 1/3 cup of mix per cup of hot water.

title: biscotti
directions: Mix sugar, nuts, butter, aniseed, anisette, water and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder and stir into mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 3 hrs.

title: monster cookies
directions: In a large bowl or dishpan, beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients in order, mixing thoroughly (easiest to mix with your hands after the oatmeal goes in!).
Use ice cream scoop to put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
The uncooked dough freezes well and cooks best when thawed to room temperature.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Roll into small balls.
Place on wax paper and chill in refrigerator.
Mix chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler and melt.
Use toothpicks to dip each ball in chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper to cool.
Ready to eat.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together with
a fork, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
With a pastry blender, cut in margarine and shortening until the mixture looks like small peas. In a small bowl, whip with a fork the beaten egg and milk.
Pour the mixture from the small bowl into the large bowl and lightly stir with a fork.
Lightly flour the counter and pour mixture out on the counter and knead about 12 times.
With a light amount of shortening (if needed), roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness. Carefully cut 9 biscuits as close together as possible and bake at 425° on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes.
Slice strawberries on a cutting board and put in bowl with about 2 tablespoons sugar, or to your taste.
Split open biscuits and put strawberries inside and on top.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: teriyaki roast beef
directions: Set oven to 325°.
Place meat in a plastic bag and set in a deep bowl.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream sugar with butter and eggs.
Add flour, cinnamon and cloves.
Add two cups raw apples plus diced dates (I use raisins). Add nuts, hot water and soda, dissolved in very small amount of hot water.
Beat well.
Bake at 350°.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Cool. Then add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Stir and mix well.
Pour into large mold or bowl.
Chill.
Use a large bowl to mix this in.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together.
Use round pump bread.
Slice off the top and pull out insides.
Pour dip into hollow bread and serve.

title: ham and broccoli in savory sauce
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Drain. Separately blend flour and butter. Add milk and cheese.
Cook, stirring, until thickened. Add broccoli and ham.
Heat.
Blend in sour cream, but do not boil. Serve over rice.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Add banana, oil, pineapple and juice, vanilla and eggs to dry ingredients; stir to blend mixture (do not beat).
Pour into greased angel food pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Set aside to cool on rack without removing from pan.
Serve plain, with whipped cream, ice cream or favorite topping.

title: black bean pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, drain and keep warm.
Saute garlic in oil in skillet until tender.
Add lime juice and sherry, cook over high heat 5 minutes or until mixture is reduced to 1/4 cup.
Add green onions and chopped tomato. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Stir in black beans and next 3 ingredients.
Pour over pasta, toss to coat.
Sprinkle with parsley, serve immediately.

title: spinach salad with hot bacon dressing
directions: Mix together.
Serve with Hot Bacon Dressing.

title: beef jerky
directions: Partially freeze meat to make slicing easier. Trim fat and gristle from flank steak. Cut meat with grain into very thin slices. Combine onion, thyme, bay leaves, salt, garlic, pepper, cloves, vinegar, wine, and Worcestershire and soy sauces. Pour marinade over steak strips to cover and marinate in the refrigerate for about 15 hours. Squeeze marinade from meat by rolling strips with a rolling pin. Place meat on baking sheets or an oven rack and dry at 175 degrees F for about 9 hours, turning once. If using a rack, place foil under it to catch the drippings. Makes 40 to 50 strips.

title: walnut turkey stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, heat butter and add sage, thyme, celery and onion; saute 5 to 7 minutes, until onion is tender.
Add bouillon cube and boiling water; stir.
Add salt, pepper, cheese and parsley.

title: marinated fried chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Season with a mixture of 2 teaspoons salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix together the vermouth, lemon juice, olive oil, thyme and parsley.
Marinate the chicken in the mixture for 1 hour.
Drain chicken well.
Roll in the flour mixed with the remaining salt, then the eggs and finally the bread crumbs.
Melt the butter in a large skillet and cook the chicken until browned and tender.
Turn the pieces frequently.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix for 10 minutes and refrigerate.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add 2 cups cold water. Add remaining ingredients and chill until firm.

title: easy spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain thoroughly.
Mix with yogurt and soup mix.
Mix crumbs and Parmesan cheese and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli pasta
directions: Cook broccoli and pasta separately. When pasta and broccoli are done, mix together. Add Parmesan garlic sauce. Mix well and serve. If you like, sprinkle with Parmesan or Romano cheese.

title: beef mushroom loaf
directions: Drain mushrooms; reserve liquid.
Add enough milk to mushroom liquid to make 1/2 cup.
In mixing bowl, combine liquid, egg, Worcestershire sauce, seasonings and bread crumbs.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in beef and mushrooms.
Mix.
Shape into loaf in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Combine ketchup and corn syrup.
Brush on meat top.
Bake meat loaf for 15 more minutes.

title: 3 bean or "calico" salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper good and pour over vegetables.
Stir or turn once or twice so the sauce can penetrate all vegetables.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.
(Make the day before using, turn often.)

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Stir in tomato paste, onion and seasoning.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Cook over heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place biscuits in a greased muffin tin, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into biscuit-lined cups.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ham, egg, cheese boats
directions: Halve bread lengthwise.
Pull out some of the insides to make shallow hollows.
Broil bread boats 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir mustard and pepper into mayonnaise.
Mash eggs in bowl.
Add ham, green pepper and mayonnaise mixture.
Spoon into bread.
Top with tomato slices and cheese.
Broil just until cheese melts.

title: decorated spice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients and set aside. Cream the butter and sugar.
Stir in corn syrup.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Roll out to 1/8-inch on floured surface.
Cut into shapes. Place on baking sheets. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes. Decorate.

title: phenomenal fudge(see's secret recipe)
directions: You will need an accurate candy thermometer and two people to beat the fudge and drop it into creamy mounds.
If you're on your own, you may want to pour the beaten fudge into a pan instead, because it sets up quickly.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 3 layers.

title: kate hepburn's brownies
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt together 2 squares of chocolate with butter in a saucepan; remove from heat.
Add 1 cup sugar, 2 eggs and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, stirring until blended.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry nut salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries.
Add to sugar; bring to boil. Dissolve jello in mixture.
Add cherries, nuts and pineapple. Allow to congeal.

title: gyoza
directions: Meat:
In a bowl, add ground pork, ginger, soy sauce, onion, cabbage, sugar, sesame oil, salt and pepper.
Stir and mix with hands until mixture becomes sticky.
Place 1 tablespoon of meat mixture in the center of each Gyoza skin.
Moisten edges of Gyoza skins with water; fold skin over meat and pinch edges to seal. Sprinkle Gyoza with cornstarch to prevent them to sticking to each other.
Makes 50 to 60 Gyoza.
Can be frozen until ready to cook.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and dry ingredients, then add all other ingredients.
Fold.
Pour into baking dish that has been greased. Dot top with butter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, stir, then bake 15 minutes longer.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well together Cool Whip, pineapple, pudding and Jell-O. Spoon into graham cracker pie crust. Chill well.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into single serving balls.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast bread and spread with 2 tablespoons butter while still hot.
Arrange toast in buttered pan and sprinkle with raisins. Beat eggs; add salt and all but 2 tablespoons sugar.
Add milk and stir to mix.
Pour over toast and let stand for 10 minutes.
Press toast down so that it soaks up most of the milk mixture.
Mix cinnamon with 2 tablespoons sugar and sprinkle over top.
Bake in 350° oven about 25 minutes until top is brown.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: hoe cakes
directions: Combine cornmeal and baking soda in medium bowl.
Add buttermilk, egg and one tablespoon melted shortening.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Heat 1 tablespoon Crisco shortening or Crisco oil on medium-high heat in heavy large nonstick skillet.
Pour 1/4 cup batter into skillet for each hoe cake.
Fry 1 to 2 minutes or until golden brown on each side. Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings. Contains 185 calories, fat 7 g (63 cal or 34% of total calories), sat fat 1 g (<5% of total calories), carb 27 g, protein 6 g, chol 35 mg and sodium 125 mg.

title: apricot crunch
directions: Combine coconut, flour, 1 cup sugar, salt and soda with butter until mixture is a coarse crumble.
Set aside 1 cup of mixture. Press remaining mixture into a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray. Spread crescent rolls in bottom of pan. Bake according to instructions on package. Set aside to cool.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown and cook steak in 2 cups water until tender (about 30 minutes). Add peppers, onions and tomatoes. Cook until peppers are tender. Thicken with flour and salt to taste.
Serve over white rice.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix boiling water, sugar, salt, and oil.
Let cool and add eggs.
Add the yeast in the warm water.
Add 7 cups flour.
Will keep a week in refrigerator.
After shaping rolls from refrigerator, let rise before baking.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon fruit compote
directions: Bring mix to boil.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat to cool 15 minutes.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, and cinnamon. Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, and vanilla and then add dry ingredients. Mix well. Stir in oats and raisins. Drop by heaping teaspoons. Bake at 350 for 8 to 10 minutes. Don't over cook.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers in salt water overnight.
Drain and dry (cut if desired).
Boil vinegar and sugar until clear.
Add cucumbers, let stand over low heat until they loose their green color.
Place 1 teaspoon spice in bottom of each quart jar.
Add pickles, cover with hot syrup and seal.

title: ground turkey and rice
directions: Mix in skillet and cook slowly until all seasonings are well blended.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and cook 3 minutes.
Cool.
Pour in baked 9-inch pie shell.
Garnish with prepared whipped topping.

title: cherry fluffs
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water; add melted butter, sugar and salt.
Blend in egg.
Gradually add sifted flour, mixing until dough is blended and soft.
Roll out dough on well-floured board. Brush lightly with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Place 1/2 of a maraschino cherry in center of each square.
Let rise until light, about 25 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: banana pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and egg yolks with about 1/4 cup of the milk.
When milk is hot, add sugar and egg yolk mixture.
Stir until thick.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Stir until oleo is melted.
Remove from heat and cool.
Use some of the cooled pudding to line inside of bowl so vanilla wafers will stick to sides.
Line bottom and sides of bowl with wafers.
Slice bananas and layer.
Add 1/2 of cooled pudding, then repeat wafers and bananas.
Top with meringue and bake in a 350° oven for 10 or 15 minutes, until brown.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut and skin chicken; arrange in baking pan.
Combine rest of ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: crumb cake
directions: In a mixing bowl combine sugar, flour and salt.
Cut in butter until mix resembles coarse meal.
Reserve 1 cup of mix and combine with cinnamon and nuts.
Set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Blend in dry ingredients sifted together.
Add mashed bananas and nuts (1/2 cup of pecans). Pour batter into a loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sausage soup
directions: Put 1/2 cup water and the sausages in a Dutch oven.
Cook 5 minutes to help cook off grease.
Remove cover and cook sausages until brown, turning frequently.
Remove sausage and slice in 1/2-inch thick slices.
Drain remaining water.
In the Dutch oven, brown onions, peppers and garlic.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes until done.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 15 to 20 minutes until browned.
Can be frozen cooked or uncooked.

title: two crust pastry
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until particles are size of small peas.
Sprinkle in water 1 tablespoon at a time, tossing with a fork until all flour is moistened and pastry almost cleans side of bowl.
(One to 2 tablespoons more water can be added if needed.)

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in cold water.
Chill until thickened.
Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Mix pineapple and bananas.
Add to jello along with marshmallows.
Mix well. Pour into a 9x13 pan and chill until firm.

title: holiday cranberry bread
directions: Grease bread pan.
In large bowl combine all ingredients except cranberries and nuts.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm or cool.

title: fresh fruit crisp
directions: Place fruit on bottom of ungreased 8 1/2 x 11 1/2 cake pan. Sprinkle gelatin over fruit.
Combine remaining ingredients in medium size bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon over fruit.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or till golden.

title: presbytery chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Make fine crumbs from the stuffing mix.
Dip breasts in first mixture, then roll in crumbs. Place in ungreased dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil for last 10 minutes of baking.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Roll graham crackers to fine consistency.
Mix with melted butter and pat in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan to form crumb crust.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir and microwave for 3 minutes on High.
Stir until foamy.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet, refrigerate and cool.
Break in pieces.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Cook sausage in skillet.
When half done, add chopped onion, pepper and peas.
Add cooked rice to mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: fried tuna
directions: Mix together and form into patties.
Brown in hot skillet with Crisco oil.
Very good with white breakfast gravy.

title: chocolate creamy cupcakes(1 gram fat)
directions: Line muffin tins with paper baking cups.
Fill each with 1/3 cup batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Prepare pudding using skim evaporated milk instead of 2 cups whole milk. Refrigerate until set, about 1 hour.
With thin sharp knife, slice off tops of cupcakes.
Spread bottom with about 1 1/2 tablespoons pudding each.
Replace tops.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges, peel and all.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Prepare Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water and sugar. Pour into ground fruit and put in containers.
Keep in refrigerator.
It will keep a long time.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, oil, sugar and 10x sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture. Stir in oatmeal, nuts and chocolate chips.
Add vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla. Mix well.
Mix dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: harvest loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease loaf pan.
Mix all dry ingredients in small bowl.
In mixer, cream butter, sugar, pumpkin and eggs; slowly add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruitcake(without the candied fruit)
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and honey.

Add dry ingredients alternately with cream. Beat in fruit and nuts. Pack into 2 greased and floured medium sized loaf or 3 small loaf pans. Place pans on middle rack of oven; place a shallow pan of hot water on the lowest rack. Bake at 300° for 60 to 65 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool completely in pan. Loosen with a knife and remove from pan. Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate animal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to chocolate mixture, stirring well.
Wrap dough in wax paper and chill 2 hours.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out each half 1/4 inch thick on a well floured cloth or board.
Keep remaining dough chilled until ready to roll.
Cut dough with animal cutters, place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool cookies on wire rack.

title: bean-cups
directions: Mix the hamburger meat with the onion, salt, pepper and egg. Take 2 tablespoons of meat and put in a deep dish.
Work the meat to make like a cup.
Take the beans with the mushroom soup and mix well.
Fill cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Good with rice or potatoes.

title: quick soup
directions: Brown ground meat, drain, then mix all ingredients in pan. Bring to a boil for about 5 min. then simmer 10 min.

title: pork barbecue
directions: In a large pot, cut up Boston butt; put in onion, vinegar, hickory smoke, oregano, cayenne pepper, red crushed pepper and garlic powder.
Cover the Boston butt with water.
Cook until tender.
Drain the Boston butt and save.
To this, add mustard and barbecue sauce and pour back over your Boston butt.

title: green tomato sweet relish
directions: Mix tomatoes, peppers, onions and salt.
Let stand for 1 hour; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Tie spices in a cloth bag and bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Pour at once into hot sterilized jars.
Makes 6 pints.

title: no bake cream cheese tart
directions: Whip Cream and set aside.
Beat Cream Cheese, Confectioner Sugar and Vanilla until smooth; fold in Whipped Cream.
Put one Vanilla Wafer in each Muffin Tin Liner.
Put a heaping teaspoon of Cream Cheese mixture over cookie and top with Pie Filling.
Makes about 12 tarts.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cook flour, eggs, sugar, water and juice until thick.
Cool and add pineapple and marshmallows.
Add 1 pint whipped cream and chill.
(May be frozen.)
Add maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: hearty baked bean casserole
directions: Brown sausages in skillet. Add ground beef, stirring until lightly browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomatoes and gravy mix.
In a 2 1/2 or 3 quart casserole, combine meat mixture with beans.
Cut onions into thick slices.
Pierce each with 3 or 4 cloves.
Arrange onion slices on top of casserole and sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 350 degrees for about 1 hour.
Serves 6-8.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Whisk ingredients together until smooth and creamy. Refrigerate.
Serve over tossed salad.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: chipmunk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
In a medium size bowl, sprinkle baking soda over dates, add hot water and set aside.
Cream the shortening, butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Sift together the flour, salt and cocoa, then add to creamed mixture and combine.
Put in the date mixture and combine.
Fold in the nuts and chocolate chips. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Let the cake cool before slicing.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Brown onion in bacon fat.
Cut chicken into serving pieces. Season and fry in bacon grease.
Pour off fat and place chicken and onion in heavy kettle.
Add water, tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook slowly over low heat for 1/2 hour.
Add lima beans, okra and corn.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add oleo and crumbs; cook 1/2 hour longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown steak in margarine in large skillet.
Add garlic salt. Cover and let simmer while preparing celery, onions and cabbage. Add to steak with Worcestershire sauce and bacon drippings.
Cook until tender, then add cooked rice.
If it seems dry, add water before adding rice so as to have some gravy.

title: walnut pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, butter, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add eggs.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
(Pecans can be substituted.))

title: good and easy quiche
directions: Spray pie pan with Pam.
Layer chilies, then cheese in pan. Beat rest of ingredients together and pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with picante, if desired.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine.
Cool to room temperature. Drain and reserve liquid.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Prick pie crust with fork tines several times.
Prebake pastry for 5 minutes.

title: swiss almond dip
directions: Mix and put in pie plate or quiche dish.
Cover with sliced almonds.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes or bubbly.
Serve with Ritz or Town House crackers.

title: dream delight
directions: Put contents of all 3 boxes in saucepan and add 3 cups water. Bring to a boil until thickened.
Let cool completely and then add Cool Whip, oranges and pineapple.
Refrigerate.

title: angel flakes(blue ribbon recipe)
directions: For sour milk, use 3/4 tablespoon white vinegar.

title: french waffles
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla and flour.
Mix.
Put teaspoons on hot waffle iron. Cooking time varies according to your iron.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix spinach, soup and stuffing mix. Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Cover with more stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until bubbly.

title: red cabbage with apples and red wine
directions: Place rice on bottom of large ungreased casserole.
In a separate bowl, stir together all other ingredients and pour over the rice.
Cover and cook in a 400° oven for 2 hours.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Fry pork chops until brown.
Place in a large baking pan.
Add the other 3 ingredients and 2 1/2 cups water; stir with a spoon until soup and water are mixed.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Check occasionally to see that chops do not stick to bottom of pan.

title: shrimp with capers and dijon mustard
directions: In heavy skillet, heat oil.
Add shallots and cook slowly until softened.
Add shrimp and cook just until they turn pink and curl.
Add mustard, pepper and capers.
Toss to coat the shrimp. Remove shrimp to a serving dish.
Add wine to skillet, increase heat and stir rapidly, scraping the pan.
Pour sauce over shrimp.

title: california rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and margarine. Remove skillet from heat and stir in all other ingredients but peppers and cheese. Lightly grease a 13x9 pan. Lay half of rice mixture in casserole then top with half of pepper and half of the cheese. Repeat with second layer of rice, peppers and cheese. Bake uncovered at 375 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown meats together over medium heat in skillet.
Drain. Cube cheese and add to meat until melted.
Add seasonings and mix well.
Spread on slices of bread and freeze on cookie sheet. Package together when frozen.
To serve, place back on cookie sheet and broil 5 minutes.
(Makes a lot of tasty snacks which are adequate for a meal when served with a vegetable tray.)

title: calico beans
directions: Cook meat, onions and peppers; add other ingredients and stir. Drain kidney and butter beans; add all beans last and stir gently so you don't smash them.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry dream pie
directions: Arrange strawberries in bottom of pie shell.
Mix cream cheese until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, blending well. Add vanilla. Fold in whipped topping and spoon into pie shell over berries. Chill at least 3 hours.
Garnish with additional berries, if desired.

title: batter fried chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and egg gradually to make batter.
Dip chicken into the batter.
Fry in large skillet with oil of your choice (I use Crisco), about 15 to 20 minutes or until nice and brown.

title: chicken delight
directions: In oil cook chicken breast (may be sliced in strips also). Cook rice by directions on package.
Combine soups, sour cream and garlic with rice and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quail breasts with rice
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour, salt, basil and pepper in regular size oven cooking bag.
Shake breasts one at a time in flour mixture to coat evenly.
Remove and set aside.
Place bag with remaining flour mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add mushrooms, onion, water, bouillon and Worcestershire sauce to bag.
Turn to mix and set aside.
Saute breasts in butter until brown.
Place on top of vegetables in bag.
Close bag with tie.
Make 6 one-half inch slits in top of bag.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until meat is done.
Combine hot rice and vegetables.
Press into small bowl. Unmold on serving platter and place breasts around rice.
Serve with sauce left in cooking bag.

title: corn relish
directions: Husk and silk corn.
Cook in boiling water for 5 minutes. Plunge into cold water.
Drain.
Cut corn from cobs.
Do not scrape cobs.
Measure 8 cups cut corn in 8 to 10-quart kettle or Dutch oven.
Combine celery, red pepper, green pepper and onion.
Add sugar, vinegar, celery seed, 2 cups water and 2 tablespoons salt. Bring vegetable mixture to boiling.
Boil uncovered for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend flour, dry mustard and turmeric with 1/2 cup cold water.
Add along with corn to boiling mixture. Return to cook and stir 5 minutes.
Pack loosely into jar, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust lids; process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes 7 pints.

title: knock your socks off cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
While hot from the oven, poke holes in cake with a fork.
Pour the Eagle Brand milk over hot cake and then pour the caramel topping over this.
After cake is cool, top with the Cool Whip and the crushed bars of candy.
MMM good.
This cake will keep in fridge for a week.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix together and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add 3 tablespoons peach jello.
Cool.
Slice peeled peaches and pour the jello mixture over them.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: friendship tea
directions: Combine cranberry juice, water, orange juice, sugar, cinnamon and cloves in medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Let steep 5 minutes; remove tea bags and spices with a spoon.
Carefully pour hot tea mixture into carafe and seal. This can be served hot or cold and is delicious either way. 6 servings.

title: white chocolate cheesecake with raspberry sauce
directions: Beat softened cheese until smooth and creamy; add 1 cup sugar, vanilla and egg.
Stir in by hand.
Stir in melted chocolate.
Pour into buttered spring-form pan.
Place in larger pan filled with water (no more than 2/3 up sides of pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian vegetables
directions: Wash and clean first 5 ingredients.
Chop potatoes.
Mix together and add remaining ingredients; mix and cook.
Can wrap in foil and cook on a grill or bake, covered, in oven at 350°.
Cook until tender, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: apple betty
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole.
Cover bottom with cake crumbs.
Add apples, sugar, cinnamon and fruit juice.
Repeat, alternating layers of crumbs with layers of apples and spices.
Top with cake crumbs.
Drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with sugar; slightly moisten with fruit juice.
Bake 3/4 hour at 375°.
Test for doneness.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: boston brown bread muffins(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pam spray a 12 cup muffin tin.
Mix together flours, cornmeal and baking soda in large bowl until blended.
In a small bowl, combine egg, molasses, brown sugar, oil and buttermilk.
Stir or beat to blend.
Stir the egg mixture into the flour mixture and mix well.
Add raisins and stir.
Fill muffin tins about 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until a tester comes out clean when inserted into the center of a muffin.
Don't overbake.
Serve hot.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: sweet-n-sour green beans
directions: Boil green beans in their juice for 15 minutes.
Drain. Layer beans and chopped onions in a dutch oven.
In small sauce pan, boil vinegar and sugar.
Pour over beans and onions.
Place in 150° oven overnight or for 6-8 hours.
Cook bacon and sprinkle over hot beans.
Toss well and add a little bacon on top for looks.
Serves 8.
To serve 10-12 people, add 2 additional cans of beans only and use the same amount of other ingredients.

title: chicken on the grill
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken.
Prick chicken with fork.
Pour mixture over chicken and marinate overnight. Cook on grill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and roll into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: white wedding punch
directions: Chill all juices until extremely cold.
Add juices and ginger ale to punch bowl.
Put some scoops of ice cream in punch bowl and serve.
Serves 30 to 35.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Melt cheeses in double boiler or over very low heat to melt. Add soup and broccoli to cheese mixture.
Cook until broccoli thaws.
Keep warm in chafing dish.
Serve with corn tortilla chips.

title: more
directions: Brown chuck.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
This freezes very well.

title: the abdullah appetizer
directions: Boil water in large casserole.
Add macaroni; cook until tender.
Drain water from macaroni.
Mix sour cream, mustard and mayonnaise in a bowl.
Mix with macaroni.
Chop up pink salmon; mix it together and serve.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: maria's rice casserole
directions: Do not cook rice.
Put all ingredients into an ovenproof baking dish and mix well.
Bake at 350° until rice is done.
Top with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: pecan squares
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch square pan and set aside.
Combine eggs and flavorings; beat until thickened.
Add sugar; beat well. Combine flour, soda and salt and stir in pecans.
Add to mixture and beat well.
Pour mixture into buttered pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325° or until done.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar; cut into 16 squares.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, margarine and vanilla in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat until mixture is cool and thick enough to spread.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown turkey; drain.
Add all ingredients except rice together until well heated; onions and celery should be tender-crisp.
Mix in rice and serve.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Brown meat, garlic, salt and pepper. Mix rice and tomato sauce.
Line greased casserole with a layer of cabbage.
Spread meat mixture over cabbage.
Repeat with layer of cabbage and pour spaghetti sauce over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 55 minutes in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
Serves about 6.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Stir the yeast in the warm water and let stand until it dissolves.
Mix the milk, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Add the dissolved yeast and mix well.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead until it bounces back when touched with a finger.
Place dough in a buttered bowl and turn to grease completely.
Cover with plastic wrap and put in warm place to rise until doubled in bulk (about one hour). Punch down and cover again with wrap.
Refrigerate covered until ready to bake.
Roll into 2 1/2 inch balls and bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire rack.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush Oreo cookies.
Mix in melted margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with 1/2 gallon soft vanilla ice cream. Freeze.
Spread with one jar ice cream topping (fudge caramel or hot fudge).
Spread with crushed salted peanuts.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Keep in freezer.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: In a large stockpot, combine shanks, water, bouillon and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove shanks and bay leaves; cut meat into cubes.
Discard bones.
Cool stock; skim fat from surface.
Add meat, carrots, celery, onions and thyme; simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Add macaroni and zucchini.
Cook 10 minutes longer or until tender.
Makes approximately 9 quarts.

title: dutch rhubarb custard(germany)
directions: Cut rhubarb into small pieces.
Mix the sugar, cornstarch and eggs (reserve the white of 1 egg).
Add the rhubarb and bake custard style on pie crust, in medium hot oven at 350°.
When finished and pie is cool, beat egg white until stiff.
Add powdered sugar and mix until peaks form.
Place this on top of pie and return to oven and brown.

title: red snapper with matchstick vegetables
directions: You will need 6 pieces parchment paper (about 9 x 12-inches) and 6 pieces string (6 inches long).

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Make dough into small balls.
Press down with a fork.
Place 1/2 pecan on each cookie. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Slice beets and drain juice.
Save liquid.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; blend well.
Add 1 1/2 cups beet juice and vinegar.
Cook until juice is thickened (about 10 minutes).
Add beets and heat thoroughly.
Serve with butter topping.

title: our yummy lasagna
directions: Boil and drain lasagna noodles as directed on box.
In a large bowl, mix egg, cottage cheese and Ricotta cheese.
Fry hamburger and drain.
Mix hamburger with sauce.
Spray 13 x 9-inch cake pan with cooking spray.
Start your first layer with noodles.
Second layer hamburger/spaghetti sauce mixture.
Third layer cottage cheese/Ricotta/egg mixture.
Top 3rd layer with Mozzarella cheese. Repeat last 4 steps (should use all of mixtures).
Save a small portion of Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
Spread sauce on top layer of noodles and top with remainder of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: In a bowl, stir soup, soy sauce, ginger, garlic and cornstarch until smooth; set aside.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown beef; drain well.
Stir in garlic powder and pepper. Spread evenly in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread corn evenly over meat.
Mash potatoes with milk, sour cream and butter. Spread mashed potatoes over corn.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with Cheddar cheese and gravy.
Serves 3 to 5.

title: goodie bars
directions: Beat together 1st 3 ingredients until it sticks together. Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: plum cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and oil and stir until smooth. Add flour, baby food and spices. Fold in nuts. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°. Glaze with mixture of juice of one lemon and cup of powdered sugar.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Remove sausage from casing.
Cook sausage, ground beef and onion in a large skillet over medium heat, stirring until meat crumbles. Drain mixture and return to skillet. Stir in marinara sauce and ziti.
Layer half of ziti mixture and half of Mozzarella cheese in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining ziti mixture over Mozzarella cheese and cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove foil. Add remaining Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 10 additional minutes.

title: quick chicken cacciatore
directions: In a large skillet, saute green pepper, onion and mushrooms in olive oil for 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Place the chicken breasts over the vegetables.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: At least 1 hour or up to 1 day before serving, drain pimiento and reserve 2 teaspoons.
In medium bowl, mix pimiento, artichokes, mayonnaise, green chilies, Jack cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Spoon into a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese and reserved pimientos. If making ahead, cover and refrigerate.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish; bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
If more liquid is needed, use chicken broth.

title: corey's stuffed mushroom
