directions: Take the stems off the mushrooms; set the caps aside. Brush the mushroom caps with olive oil. Chop 2 to 3 of the mushroom stems. Saute garlic, onion, olive oil and the chopped mushroom stems. Add sausage to the garlic/onion mixture. Cook until sausage is thoroughly cooked.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, combine oats and milk.
Set aside until milk is absorbed.
In a medium bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add butter, egg and bananas to oat mixture.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Stir in seeds or raisins.
Fill greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pans or paper cups 2/3 full.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Makes 12.

title: taco salad
directions: Add taco seasoning to ground beef.
Fill the envelope with water; add to mixture.
Turn to low heat and add soup; mix together and continue cooking until soup is melted.
Stir often. In a large bowl, chop lettuce.
Add anything you like in a salad, tomatoes, onion, black olives, etc.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Blend well. Stir in flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Do not beat!
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 325° in greased and floured loaf pan or Bundt pan for one hour or until done.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans, brown sugar and mustard together.
In another bowl, mix bacon and ketchup.
Place half of bean mixture in a casserole dish and place 1/2 of bacon and ketchup mix on top.
Add the rest of the bean mixture and add remainder of bacon mixture on top. Bake in 325° oven (uncovered) about 2 hours.
It will get nice and brown when done.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Beat egg whites
until	foamy.	Add
salt
and cream of tartar; beat until	stiff.	Add sugar, 3 tablespoons at a time and beat 2 minutes
each
time you add sugar.
Add vanilla and beat until very	stiff.	Stir
in
chocolate
chips
and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls
onto	cookie	sheet
covered with foil. Preheat oven to	350°
to
375° (depending on your oven).
Put cookies into oven
and
turn
off heat.	Leave overnight or at least 8 hours. Do not open oven within that time.

title: green bean soup
directions: Boil ham hocks.
When done (meat falling off), take out of water.
Put potatoes and green beans in water and boil until done. Drain.

title: creamy chicken primavera
directions: Saute chicken over medium heat in margarine. Add pasta and vegetables and water.
Cover and cook on medium heat 8 minutes until crisp-tender.
Stir occasionally. Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly. Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn, hominy and chilies of all juices.
Place all in baking dish with cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well-beaten egg yolks.
Then alternately add milk and flour, which has been sifted with the baking powder.
Then add stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla extract.
Bake in two 9-inch layer pans, greased and lined on bottom with waxed paper, in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fast coconut pie
directions: Blend everything in a blender.
Pour in a buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake until custard sets, at 400°, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: haystack candy
directions: Melt first two ingredients in double boiler, then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop on wax paper in small stacks.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers but do not pare.
Slice crosswise.
Slice onions also.
Mix salt with the 3 vegetables.
Bury 1 quart of cracked ice in mixture; cover and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.

title: cranberry poppy seed loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, poppy seed and baking powder; set aside.
Blend milk, margarine, egg, vanilla and lemon peel; stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Stir in cranberries; spread in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Drizzle with glaze, if desired. Yield: 1 loaf.

title: lemon or lime pie
directions: Combine all ingredients very well with a wire whisk.
Put into pie shells and chill.

title: oregano bread and elderberry jelly
directions: Boil fruit to release juice with small amount of water.
Mash with potato masher after 10 minutes and remove from heat; strain. If less than 3 cups juice, add 1/2 to 1 cup water and allow to run through seeds again.
Follow instructions for Sure-Jell jelly. Serve on toasted bread.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain noodles, then rinse with cold water.
Prepare dressing mix by directions on package.
Cut up tomatoes, cucumbers and onions.
Mix all together with noodles and refrigerate overnight.

title: mandarin orange cake(for a special occasion)
directions: Mix all together for 2 minutes.
Bake in three 9-inch round pans, greased and floured or may use one 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes.
Frost and store in refrigerator 8 hours.

title: fruitcake
directions: With pastry brush, grease pan well with softened butter or use brown paper to line pan.
Cut up fruit and put in one bowl.
Leave cherries whole.

title: vegetable basil soup
directions: In a 5-quart pan over medium heat, cook onion, celery and carrot in butter, stirring occasionally, until onion is soft, but not browned.
Add potato, tomatoes, broth and basil.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cauliflower and zucchini; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add peas and simmer until tender (about 5 minutes).
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pass Parmesan at the table.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: easy spaghetti bake
directions: Mix noodles and hamburger with the spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, green pepper and onions; spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: one dish ham bake
directions: Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, ham and onion powder in ungreased rectangular baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Mix baking mix and milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Bake 30 minutes at 450° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand at least 5 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cherry bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla, baking powder, flour and milk.
Alternate flour and milk when adding.
Stir remaining ingredients with a spoon and add to first mixture.
Bake in greased and floured jelly roll pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Drizzle top with powdered sugar frosting.

title: tommaso's marinara sauce
directions: Place olive oil in medium size saucepan and heat until almost smoking. Add onion, garlic, celery, carrots and bell pepper and saute until semi-cooked.
Add tomatoes, parsley, herbs and vermouth. Simmer 30 to 45 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste. Serve over pasta of choice. Sprinkle top with freshly grated imported Romano or Parmesan cheese.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage and spread in greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Stir in cooked rice and salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture over cabbage.
Heat tomato soup and water to boiling.
Pour over all ingredients.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350.

title: oven stew
directions: Cut vegetables into suitable pieces.
Mix all ingredients in Dutch oven that has been soaked in water.
Cover tightly and bake 4 hours at 300° in preheated oven.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Pour beans into slow cooking pot; add water.
Soak overnight or at least 6 hours.
Cover pot and cook on high for 2 to 3 hours or until beans are tender.
Drain, saving liquid.
Mix 1 cup of liquid with salt, molasses, mustard, brown sugar and onion.
Cut salt pork into 2 or 3 pieces.
In slow cooking pot, combine drained beans with mixture and pork.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix flour, mayonnaise and milk together. Bake in greased muffin tins until golden brown. Bake at 450°.

title: tea punch
directions: Boil tea bags in water and add to sugar until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and finish filling with water.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: fabulous french dressing
directions: Mix together the garlic, sugar, Lawry's salt, Accent, pepper and tarragon with the wine vinegar and olive oil.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine mayo, flour, eggs and milk until well blended.
Stir in onions and crabmeat.
Add cheese.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: blueberry dream pie
directions: Cream the cheese with confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Fold the whipping cream in the cheese mixture; pour into baked pie shell and refrigerate.
Put berries, sugar, salt, lemon juice and cinnamon in saucepan and cook slow until berries are soft.
Add cornstarch mixture and cook 5 minutes until thick.
Cool.
When cool, spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and keep in refrigerator.
Makes 8 delicious servings.

title: easy taco soup
directions: In a large pot, saute onion and beef until well browned.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, beans and seasonings.
Add some water for desired thickness.
Cook 20 minutes on low.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Cover ribs with water in a roasting pan.
Add lemon juice, garlic, celery, bay leaves and salt.
Bake about 1 hour until just tender at 350°.
Drain and brush on barbecue sauce and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes until very tender.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil with onion, green and red pepper. Stir in tomatoes and chicken broth.
Add turkey sausage and vinegar.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add black beans and simmer 5 more minutes.
Serve over cooked white or brown rice.
Serves 8.

title: taco salad(serves 8)
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add the package of taco mix.
Drain. Refrigerate until chilled or overnight.
Add chopped tomatoes, torn lettuce and broken chips.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and toss with bottled dressing.
Top with sliced avocados.
Serve immediately.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut and reserve juice.
Combine sugar, vinegar and kraut juice in a pot.
Bring to a boil until sugar dissolves. Set aside and let cool.
Combine sauerkraut and chopped vegetables.
Pour cooled mixture over sauerkraut.
Toss well. Cover and chill.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple.
Add pecans and marshmallows. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Combine ingredients and let stand out all day.
Refrigerate after 8 to 12 hours.
After 3 days take out and feed.

title: savannah bread
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Add baking powder, salt and soda. Sift again. Cream shortening and peanut butter together thoroughly.
Gradually add sugar, continuing to cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.

title: janie's cranberry relish-salad
directions: Cook cranberries with small amount of water until cranberries are cooked. Add sugar and pineapple. Combine Jell-O and hot water until dissolved. Combine Jell-O with cranberry mixture. Add nuts and celery. Chill and serve.

title: fig preserve cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, milk, and eggs.
Sift in flour and spices, then add vanilla.
Fold in pecans and figs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: lemon love
directions: Soak gelatine in small amount of water.
In double boiler, cook sugar, egg yolks, juice and rind of lemon until it coats the spoon (custard, 10 minutes and stir).
Add gelatine; take from heat. Cool slightly.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in sherbets. Makes 5 plus.

title: white decorator frosting
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix together, adding the water.
Stir until well combined but do not overbeat!

title: date nut cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses together and blend in vanilla flavoring.
Add nuts and mix thoroughly.
Mold into a ball and let chill for 30 minutes.
Chopped pecans should be place on waxed paper and then roll cheese ball to coat thoroughly with nuts.
Chill until ready to use.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: Chop tomatoes in 1/4-inch pieces. Put in bowl.
Chop onions very fine.
Add to tomatoes.
Crush crackers very fine.
Add to tomatoes.
Pour butter, salt and lots of pepper. Mix.
Add buttermilk and mix well. Pour into 2-quart greased casserole. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Brown under broiler, if necessary. Serves 6 to 8.

title: casserole italiano
directions: In skillet, brown beef with onion, garlic and seasonings. Stir to separate meat.
Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole with soup, water and noodles.
Place cheese around edge of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until foamy.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together in a plastic bag.
Put pecans in a large bowl.
Pour egg white over nuts and turn over until nuts are all glossy.
Pour sugar over the nuts and turn over until all nuts are covered. Spread nuts on a very liberally buttered cookie tin with 4 sides. Put in 250° oven for 1 hour.
But every 15 minutes, turn nuts over on the tin so all get coated.
At end of 1 hour, turn off oven but keep nuts in oven until oven is cold.
This makes them crisper.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir meat and onion in butter until onion is tender. Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat and stir in soup; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat through using low heat. Serve over noodles, rice, mashed potatoes or toast.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients with 8 cups water.
Serves 10.
Use 3 tablespoons per individual serving.

title: skillet potatoes au gratin
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in skillet and cover, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Mix cream or milk, butter and cheese with potatoes.
Cook, uncovered, on low heat for 10 minutes.
Top with bacon bits.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour orange juice over apples.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Cook until when dropped in a cup of cold water it will crack or pop.
Then add raw peanuts and cook until peanuts look roasted and golden brown.
Add butter, vanilla and soda.
Stir down until it quits foaming.
Pour out on buttered pan.

title: lemon cloud pie
directions: In
saucepan, combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, water, lemon rind, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat; stir constantly	until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add 4 ounces cream cheese; blend well.
Beat egg whites.
Add 1/2 cup sugar (beat stiff).
Fold into lemon mixture.
Spoon into pie shell; chill for 2 hours.

title: golden rice(serves 6)
directions: Rinse rice (basmati) in several changes of water before cooking.
In a 2-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, bring chicken stock and water to a boil.
Add rice, cinnamon, bay leaf and salt.
Stir.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes. Add turmeric or saffron and stir lightly with a fork.
Continue to cook, covered, over low heat another 10 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Remove cinnamon stick and bay leaf. Sprinkle with almonds and serve hot.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Mix well, oil, sugar, eggs and molasses together.
Sift together, flour, salt, cream of tartar, cloves, cinnamon, ginger and allspice.
Add to molasses mixture.
Bake at 350° for seven minutes.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: old fashion oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water over medium heat until raisins are plump (about 15 minutes).
Drain raisins, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to reserved liquid to measure 1/2 cup.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in reserved liquid.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Cook raisins in water.
Sweeten with sugar.
Add crushed pineapple and lemon or orange juice.
Cook until tender.
Thicken with cornstarch.

title: marinated cheese
directions: Cube block of Cheddar cheese and block of cream cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cheese.
Let marinate overnight.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.
Beautiful served in a glass bowl.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in the cup of milk on very low heat; let cool.
Add yeast mixture to cooled milk.
Beat eggs, sugar and salt and add to the liquid mixture.
Stir in flour, but not until smooth.
Cover and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Coat Bundt pan with the other 1/2 stick margarine (use it all).
Pour mixture in Bundt pan and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry marzipans
directions: Use a different Jell-O flavor if you like and shape like that fruit.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni according to package. Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients all together. Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: energy bars
directions: Toast oats in shallow pan in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until brown, stirring often.
Line 9-inch square pan with foil or grease. Melt marshmallows, peanut butter, honey and margarine over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in toasted oats.
Add raisins, if desired.
Place in pan spreading evenly. Chill until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: melting moments
directions: In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, cream butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in flour and cornstarch until well mixed.
Wrap and refrigerate dough at least 2 hours.
Preheat oven at 325°.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until firm and golden.
Cool slightly and remove to wire rack until cool.
Meanwhile, in bowl mix remaining powdered sugar with orange juice.
Makes 1 cup glaze.
Place wax paper under rack to catch drips and spoon on glaze.
Let dry on racks.

title: marge's carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots 8 to 10 minutes; drain and add onion and green pepper.
Whip remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables. Marinate several hours or overnight.
Keeps in airtight container in refrigerator 2 weeks or longer.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cut onions into 1-inch pieces.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add green onions.
Top with cover; process until chopped.
Remove cover; add cottage cheese and yogurt.
Top with cover; process one minute or until smooth.
Remove top; add spinach, lime juice and seasonings.
Top with cover and pulse two or three times or until mixed well.
Chill until serving time.

title: banana bread
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Cream together butter and sugar. Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: crunchies
directions: Melt chips over hot, not boiling water.
Add last 3 ingredients to melted butterscotch chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: basic corn bread
directions: Mix up a cornbread batter and add a small can of whole kernel corn (drained).
Mix and pour half of batter in a well-greased skillet.
Brown 1/2 to 3/4 pound hamburger meat.
Drain off grease. Sprinkle over corn bread batter to within 1 inch of edge of skillet.
Top with Velveeta cheese, still keeping from within 1 inch of edge of skillet.
Top this with the other half of cornbread mixture.
Bake in 400° oven until brown.
If you desire it to be hot, a few jalapeno peppers can be added to browned hamburger meat.

title: country spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in cooking pan.
Mix all ingredients together, except onions.
Pour mixture over spareribs, then place onions on top.
Cover pan with lid and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet to make crust.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown. Let cool. Cream together cream cheese, dressing and mayonnaise.
Spread on baked crust.
Cut vegetables into small pieces and layer on top of cream cheese mixture.
Then top with shredded cheese.
This is excellent.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Then, in a Dutch oven or large roasting pan, fry bacon until crisp; set aside.
Drain fat from pan.
In the same pan, cook and stir ground beef, onion and celery until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water; stir bouillon and remaining ingredients into meat mixture.
Then cover.

title: steamed salmon with potato gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes, milk, cream and garlic in a large saucepan.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Transfer potato-cream mixture to a 9 x 12-inch gratin dish and bake for 10 minutes.

title: coffee cream frosting
directions: Combine sugar, coffee, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add butter and beat until smooth and creamy.
Spread over cake when cooled.

title: fabulous fruit dip
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and either nutmeg or ginger. Mix together well.
Pour into serving bowl and refrigerate until ready to use.
Serve in center of tray, surrounded by fruit.

title: easy candy
directions: Mix sugar and syrup; bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter and cornflakes; mix.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water about 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Do not overcook.
Cool and peel; quarter potato and slice thinly.
Set aside.
Fry bacon and onion together in large skillet until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Add flour, sugar, salt, pepper and bacon drippings.
Heat, stirring constantly until bubbly.
Add water and vinegar.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gently stir in potato slices and heat through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush cookies and place 1/2 of them in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together Cool Whip, cream, butter and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding and milk in separate bowl.
Combine both mixtures and pour over crumbs.
Spread rest of crumbs on top.
Chill a few hours.

title: punch slush
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add sugar and Kool-Aid. Add rest of water, then add pineapple juice to make 1 gallon. Place in freezer about 8 hours before serving time.
After 2 hours, start to stir mixture about every 45 minutes.
Add 7-Up when ready to serve.

title: bean delight tonight(working family)
directions: Don't drain the kidney beans!
Brown the hamburger or ground beef; add the onion and garlic.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Add the beans; continue heating.
I forgot, drain the ground beef. Serves 3 generously.
So quick, simple and delicious.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, butter and Worcestershire sauce until well blended.
Add celery salt, radish and onions, mix well. Chill to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken smit
directions: Place deboned breasts in casserole dish with 1/2 stick butter. Sprinkle with garlic salt, paprika and pepper.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Saute onion in other 1/2 butter.
In bowl, mix soup, sour cream, onions and a little juice from cooked breasts.
Mix well.
Place cooked chicken back into casserole.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake another 20 to 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly. Serve over rice.

title: hors d'oeuvre cocktail meatballs to freeze
directions: Thoroughly mix ground beef, onion, garlic, cornflakes and eggs; season to taste.
Shape into walnut-size balls.
Combine remaining ingredients in a heavy skillet or pan.
Simmer 5 minutes, place meatballs in sauce and cook slowly 1 hour.
Cool and refrigerate until fat hardens.
Skim off and discard fat.
Pour meatball mixture into containers and freeze.
Reheat to serve.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine powdered sugar, Cool Whip, and cream cheese.
Mix well. Chill before serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together; put into casserole dish and then add topping.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in sugar. Slowly add brandy and rum.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, whipped cream and milk to thin. Place in punch bowl; sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until thoroughly mixed. Blend half of mixture at a time in a blender until smooth.
Yield: About 3 cups.

title: mock stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, brown meat over medium heat.
Add soup, water, mixed vegetables, mushrooms, macaroni
and seasonings. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until macaroni is tender.
Remove from heat; stir in yogurt.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until heated through.
Per serving:
About 390 cals:
20 g. protein:
15 g. fat:
41 g. carb:
1119 mg. sodium.
Preparation:
10 minutes. Total time:
20 minutes.

title: swedish sweet rolls
directions: Mix flour, butter and sugar as for pie. Add eggs, milk and yeast.
Mix together.
Mix in another cup of flour.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Divide in fifths.
Roll in 9-inch cake. Spread with melted butter. Cut in eighths like for pie.
Roll from outer edge.
Let rise. Bake and cool.
Frost as desired.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter and add to brown sugar.
Stir until well mixed.
Allow to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add chopped pecans and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan, 11 x 15-inch.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. When almost cool, cut into squares.

title: layered dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of pan.
Next, spread chili on top of cheese, then put black olives on top of chili.
Heat.
Last put Monterey cheese on top.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix 1 cup brown sugar, 2 cups water, and 2 Tbsp. margarine and bring to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes. Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2 inch baking dish. Mix the biscuit mix, raisins, chopped pecans, 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1/3 cup water together and pour over syrup mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: blackberry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sort through berries to remove any bruised or moldy ones.
Toss good berries with flour, sugar and orange rind.
Place in an 8-inch baking dish.

title: kool-aid sherbet
directions: Mix ingredients and freeze.
Simple, but wonderful for kids!

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut any shape you desire.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Blend cheese, margarine and flour.
Wrap mixture around dry olives.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, leaving one-inch in between each olive.
Enjoy!!!

title: corn beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix all ingredients.
Add macaroni.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top of casserole and add slices of butter on top. Bake at 375 degrees for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: In large baking dish, mix rice, water and cream of chicken soup.
Add chicken on top.
Shake seasoned salt over chicken and rice.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix ingredients sparingly, cool in refrigerator and serve.

title: amanda's brownies
directions: Mix eggs with electric mixture until frothy.
Add everything. Cook at 200° for 4 hours.
When done, put favorite frosting.
Let it melt until gooey, then eat.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy, 2-quart saucepan.
Heat slowly while stirring until all sugar is melted.
Continue to cook, stirring, over medium heat until a firm ball forms in cold water or 234° on candy thermometer.
Mixture must be cooked slowly and stirring constantly to avoid overcooking.
Remove from heat.
Add a small pinch of soda, 2 teaspoons of vanilla and pecans.
Beat at high speed until ready to pour into a 7 x 11-inch buttered pan.
Allow to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: easy barbecued chicken
directions: Wash chicken and paper towel dry.
Season with minced garlic, salt, pepper and red pepper flakes.
Brush olive oil on a clean grill.
Grill chicken, skin side up with the grill top down 1-2 hours.
Turn occasionally.
Chicken is done when meat is fork tender and juices run clear.
At last minute, baste with barbecue sauce (recipe to follow).

title: corn bread
directions: Mix above ingredients together and bake at 425° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dutch krakelingen
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour and milk to creamed mixture.
Chill dough for ease in handling.
Divide dough into four equal parts.
Work with one part at a time and refrigerate remaining dough.
Divide each part into 8 pieces.
Roll piece out to an 8-inch strand and twist into a pretzel shape.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Brush cookie with egg and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool on racks.
Yields 32 cookies.

title: squash souffle
directions: *You may substitute 1/4 cup warm milk.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, mixing well.
Add the dry ingredients, sifted together.
Stir in the coconut and the nuts.
Form into a roll; cover with wax paper and place in the refrigerator overnight.
Slice and bake in a moderately hot oven, 375°, for about ten minutes.
Makes about forty cookies.

title: plain cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into two 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cobblestone candy
directions: Melt chocolate in the microwave (30 seconds) on High, then stir and repeat.
When completely melted, add remaining ingredients, coating well.
Spread on Silverstone cookie sheet. Put in freezer for 5 minutes.
Break in small pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix potatoes and vanilla.
Add sugar slowly to make stiff dough.
Roll out real thin on wax paper.
Spread peanut butter and roll up like a jelly roll.
Cool 1 hour and cut in small pieces.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Note:
Hold out 1 cup cake mix for top of cake.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine with rest of ingredients except cheese.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: yummy kolbassi
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place kolbassi into baking dish. Combine chili sauce, pineapple and brown sugar.
Pour over kolbassi.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting occasionally.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done and drain. Mix other ingredients and stir or fold in cooked broccoli. Spread crumbs or ground crackers on top and dot with butter.

title: peppy potatoes pimento
directions: Prick potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Cut thin slices off tops; scoop out potatoes and mash with fork.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refill potatoes.
Reheat in a 400° oven for 10 minutes, or until heated thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Fry ground beef and chopped onion until done.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serve in electric fondue pot or other means to keep it hot.
Best when dipping taco chips.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix
cranberries
and sugar;
let stand overnight.
Mix rest of	ingredients well.
Can be frozen for a long period of time.

title: tuna muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine and mix together all ingredients except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into other mixture.
Spray muffin tins with Pam and fill tins into a mound shape.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Run a knife around each muffin to loosen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle some of the dressing crumbs on top if you like.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Melt cheese into ground beef; add other ingredients.
Serve warm.

title: jummer's cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and let set 10 minutes.
Mix Bisquick with 1/2 cup water and add to dissolved yeast.
Dough is soft, not gooey.
Divide dough into quarters and roll into rectangles.
Brush with butter.

title: mashed potato cakes
directions: Mix together.
Shape into patties.
Fry in hot oil until brown, turning once.

title: raspberry tang salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; set aside to cool.
Soften cream cheese in mayonnaise, then all other ingredients, except whipped cream are to be added.
Add this to cooled Jell-O, then fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: art salt dough
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Slowly mix in water.

title: barbecued beef(for a bunch, 24)
directions: Place beef in Dutch oven.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over beef.
Cover and bake at 350° for 5 hours, turning beef occasionally.
Shred beef with a fork.
Serve in buns for sandwiches or as desired.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat in. Add flour, vanilla, milk and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake for approximately 10 minutes or until brown.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Take stems out.
Lay aside.
Chop celery and onion fine.
Put margarine, celery and onion in skillet.
Cook until tender.
Chop stems fine.
Add to skillet.
Simmer 5 minutes. Stir in bread crumbs, sage and poultry seasoning.
Stir well.
Add egg.
Spread thin layer in glass dish.
Stuff the rest into the caps.
Lay in dish.
Put in broiler for 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat the eggs well, then stir in the milk.
Set aside.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix with the eggs and milk until smooth.
Beat in the oil and add the corn.
Drop by the spoonfuls into hot deep oil and fry until brown.
Serve either syrup or hot gravy.
Yields 12 to 14 small fritters.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook rice separately.
Chop shrimp and set aside.
Melt oleo or oil.
Add onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic in a heavy pot. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat until onions are wilted.
Add tomato paste and cook, stirring constantly, for about 15 minutes. Add 1 1/2 cups water.
Season to taste with salt and black and red peppers.
Add sugar and cook, uncovered, over medium heat for 40 minutes.
Add shrimp and continue cooking another 20 minutes. Dissolve cornstarch in 1/2 cup water and add.
Cook another 5 minutes; mix ingredients with cooked rice.
Add green onion and parsley.
Mix again.
Serves 8.

title: kolbassi hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut kolbassi into bite size pieces.
Boil 10 minutes to get grease out; drain.
Cook kolbassi with remaining ingredients for 2 hours on top of stove.

title: brown rice
directions: Bake in greased casserole, covered.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 5 minutes.
Bake in greased tube pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: kristie's potatoes
directions: Put sliced potatoes in casserole dish.
Add peppers, onions and pimientos.
Repeat the process until all ingredients are used. In saucepan, put cheese, milk and butter.
Melt and pour over potatoes.
Top with corn flakes.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rice pilaf with corn
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add cumin seed; saute 1 minute.
Add rice and next 5 ingredients.
Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add water and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, or until liquid is absorbed.
Remove pan from heat; let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Serves 5.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Divide egg yolks from whites. Combine egg yolks, water, lemon juice and cornstarch. Mix well. Cook mixture over hot water, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Boil 1 minute. Remove and stir in butter, vinegar and lemon extract. Pour in baked pie shell. Make meringue out of egg whites and sugar; put on top.

title: layered taco salad
directions: Brown meat with 1/2 the taco seasoning mix.
Mix together in a bowl the cream cheese, sour cream and the remaining half of the taco seasoning.
Layer the ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the following order:
thick layer of lettuce, cream cheese mixture, hamburger, tomato, onion, black olives, green pepper and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with taco chips and salsa sauce.
Keep refrigerated.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in well-greased casserole dish for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: candy covered peanuts
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Dissolve sugar in water in pan over medium heat.
Add food coloring.
Pour in peanuts. Cook and stir frequently until all sauce is gone.
Pour onto cookie sheet. Stir every 5 minutes for 30 minutes.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Place 1/2 frozen dough balls in a well-greased large Bundt pan.
Mix dry pudding mix, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Spoon over dough balls.
Add remaining dough balls.
Drizzle butter over balls.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Spray a sheet of plastic wrap with nonstick cooking oil and place sprayed side down over rolls.
Do not make a tight wrap.
Let stand on counter for 8 hours or overnight.
Unwrap and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes and invert on serving dish.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Remove 10 large outer leaves of cabbage; cook in boiling water for 5 to 8 minutes, until just tender.
Drain and set aside. Reserve remaining cabbage for other uses.

title: caramel nut acorns
directions: Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Melt the butter in a 2 quart saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar, vanilla, and pecans.
Add flour mixture and mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls, using a rounded teaspoon for each. Flatten one side by pressing on ungreased cookie sheet. Pinch top to resemble an acorn.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15-18 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and then dip in caramel mixture (see below).

title: chocolate fudge pizza
directions: White Chocolate Glaze or Vanilla Drizzle

title: fresh minted fruit cup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Cover and chill until about 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: baked bean trio
directions: Saute bacon and onion until bacon is crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: Cook broccoli and onion in water until tender.
Do not drain. Stir in milk and soup; heat.
Add cheese, stirring until melted. Cool slightly.
Place half at a time in blender and blend until smooth.

title: seafood and chicken lasagne
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions until soft.
Using a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, spread a small amount of Hollandaise on the bottom and place a layer of noodles on top.
Cover with half of the chicken or seafood and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Top with half of the mushrooms and onion mixture, then half of the remaining Hollandaise and sprinkle with half of the basil and oregano.
Top with half of the Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Place asparagus tips neatly in a layer over cheese.
Repeat layers ending with cheeses.
Cook uncovered in a 350° oven for 35 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve with salad with a tart dressing to offset richness.
Serves 20 to 24.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream
together
oleo
and sugar.
Add eggs, sour milk, flour, soda,
baking powder and mashed bananas.
Mix together well. Bake at 350° until done.
